@81    = ~Wow! Just my luck, real adventurers! Maybe you can help me.~
@82    = ~Thank you for rescuing me from the mines.  Now that Shikata is dead, we are one step closer to saving our people.  You have our gratitude.~
@83    = ~She grants the rescue Haer'dalis quest.~
@84    = ~Well, you see I have this secret fishing hole that no one else knows about...~
@85    = ~It's a great place! I could catch knucklehead trout almost bigger than I am!~
@86    = ~Lord Ketlaar Argrim~
@87    = ~You bet it is. People'd give a lot to know where this place is. Closer than you'd think too.~
@88    = ~No, you don't understand. I can't go there anymore and I was hoping you could help me.~
@89    = ~No, it's just across the bridge and then south, on the beach. You can't miss it. But I can't go back because of the monsters!~
@90    = ~Really big monsters! You should see 'em, they're even bigger than I am! They came down the shore and started eating all of my fish. If you can run off the monsters, I'll let you keep whatever's left of my catch. You can sell the knucklehead bone to Pomab -- it's worth a lot!~
@91    = ~I thought you could help me. Some heroes you are.~
@92    = ~Thanks for helping me out. But you better get going or those monsters will eat all of my fish!~
@93    = ~Wow, you did it! You got rid of the monsters! You really are heroes, just like Hrothgar!~
@94    = ~Help you with what?~
@95    = ~Maybe we can, maybe we can't... it depends on what you need help with.~
@96    = ~Yeah, well we're too busy. Sorry kid.~
@97    = ~Go on...~
@98    = ~Is this going to be a long story?~
@99    = ~Your secret's safe with me. Farewell, Damien.~
@100   = ~Sounds nice.~
@101   = ~I'd love to stick around and talk about fishing, but we've got to go. Farewell.~
@102   = ~That's great, but I don't think we'll be doing much fishing.~
@103   = ~Hmm... sounds fascinating, but not exactly our line. Heh heh. Good luck, son.~
@104   = ~What do you mean? Did you forget where it is?~
@105   = ~Stop a second there young'n, cuz I heard what you gone and done for old Brun.  It made me ashamed that I didn't try to help him myself.  Good to know there's still someone willin' ta go the extra mile, even for a stranger.  I want ya to have this heirloom of mine, because of what you did.  Now my heirs didn't loom so big, but you ought to get more use out o' it than my mantle does.  Folks like you make a jaded old man think there's still decent people out there.~
@106   = ~Sorry boy, we can't help you. Farewell.~
@107   = ~Monsters? What monsters?~
@108   = ~I think I've heard enough of your tall tales, boy. Run along now.~
@109   = ~Ah, I see. We get the bones you folks use for carving, and you get your fishing spot back. Very well, we'll do it.~
@110   = ~Of course we'll... Uh, just *how* big did you say those monsters were? Oh my! Look at the time. We've got to be going. Good luck, boy.~
@111   = ~We'd really like to help, but we're kind of busy. Sorry, Damien. Farewell.~
@112   = ~We have bigger fish to fry. Get lost kid.~
@113   = ~Yeah, whatever.~
@114   = ~Sorry, Damien. Maybe some other time.~
@115   = ~We're working on it. These things take time.~
@116   = ~Hey! Do you want to fight those monsters? No? All right then. Just simmer down and we'll take care of it.~
@117   = ~We're too busy to help you, sorry. Farewell.~
@118   = ~All in a day's work.~
@119   = ~Just glad we could help.~
@120   = ~That's right, we're heroes. Don't forget to tell all your friends about us.~
@121   = ~Thank you for getting rid of those monsters.  You're the greatest.  When I grow up I wanna be just like you!~
