@375   = ~Can you tell me a little about the town? ~
@376   = ~I must take my leave.  Farewell.~
@377   = ~Another dwarf in town, I see.  You with Hildreth?  I figure you dwarves might be looking to take back some of your old cities in the Spine of the World.~
@378   = ~Hildreth?~
@379   = ~No, Hildreth and I being in Easthaven is just a coincidence. ~
@380   = ~Old cities?~
@381   = ~No, actually I just wanted to ask you about Easthaven.~
@382   = ~Excellent, it's a deal then.  But before I go on my, uh, secret dwarven expedition, I wanted to ask you some things about Easthaven.~
@383   = ~Aye, I think that's her name - she came into town a few days ago.  Have to say, I thought she was a man at first, with that beard and all.  Can't see how you dwarves get used to it.  ~
@384   = ~Hildreth... I may go look for her after we speak, then.  I wanted to ask you about Easthaven first, though.~
@385   = ~What was that you said about old cities?~
@386   = ~Well met, friend.  I am Erevain Blacksheaf of Evereska.  It has been many moons since I have seen friendly faces.  Despite the dreary nature of our current locale, Easthaven is a welcome sight for these elven eyes.~
@387   = ~When I set out from Evereska, I was used to a peaceful life.  I had no idea what wonders and horrors the life of adventure would bring to my ever-changing doorstep.  I'm glad I didn't go on the Retreat twenty years ago.~
@388   = ~Yes, I am an elf.  I am "up here" because I have decided to explore the world before participating in the Retreat.~
@389   = ~Ah, I suppose it's fine.  I'm just used to the sunny climate of my homeland.  This place is like an icy anvil where the hammer of Auril smashes down upon us, leaving the landscape barren and the horizon foreboding in every direction.~
@390   = ~Answer me, Corellon... why do I always have to get the idiots?~
@391   = ~Uh... no.  I can't say that I have.  I think I have to be going now.  It was... nice talking to you, friend.  Sweet water and light laughter... I guess.~
@392   = ~The Retreat is the gradual migration of Tel'Quessir to the isle of Evermeet.  It should only take a few hundred years for all of the People to complete the migration.  Until then, I've decided to explore the rest of Faerun.~
@393   = ~You'd be surprised.  Adventure can leap out at you in the most unlikely form and at the most unexpected time.~
@394   = ~Grrrr.  GRRRRR.  NO! NO! NO!  NOOOOOO!  Why does everyone keep asking me that?!~
@395   = ~Well, I haven't heard any rumors lately.  However, when I traveled through Kuldahar, I had a strange feeling about something in that valley.  It's more than just the weather that bothered me.  Something seemed amiss in the mountains, the trees, even the clouds in the sky.  Something was out of place.  Something was... wrong.~
@396   = ~Well met, again, friends.~
@397   = ~Oh.  You again.  Leave me alone, please.  I'm not interested in talking to you.~
@398   = ~Yes.  I've heard the locals are forming an expedition into the Kuldahar Pass to investigate some problems there.  I won't be going with them, though I may pass through the area.~
@399   = ~Hello.  I'm <CHARNAME>.  Tell me, Erevain, have you seen much in your travels?~
@400   = ~An elf, eh?  What in the Nine Hells are you doing up here?~
@401   = ~Well met, brother.  How goes your journey?~
@402   = ~What's wrong with the locale?  There's nothing wrong with a little bit of chilly weather.~
@403   = ~Yeah, she's a beaut, isn't she?  Well, I must be off.  Farewell.~
@404   = ~Horse~
@405   = ~Hmph!  That's why it's called "adventure," stupid elf-person.~
@406   = ~Horror, eh?  Let me tell you about horror.  Have you ever sliced a man from his belly to his throat?  Or watched a man gasp his last breath as you hold his pulsating heart in your hand?  Well... have you?~
@407   = ~There doesn't seem to be much adventure around here, friend.~
@408   = ~Do you know of any other adventurers in Easthaven?~
@409   = ~What is "the Retreat?"~
@410   = ~Chicken~
@411   = ~Well, it was nice talking to you, but I must take my leave.  Farewell.~
@412   = ~What is "the Retreat?"~
@413   = ~Yeah, yeah, yeah.  The Retreat.  I gotcha.  So... hear any good rumors lately?~
@414   = ~Being a traveler, you must hear a lot of interesting things.  Have you heard anything interesting lately?~
@415   = ~The ranger Kivan has told us that the leader of the bandits is named Tazok.~
@416   = ~We killed Lysan, the Auril priestess, and returned to Kresselack. Unfortunately, all Kresselack could tell us was that neither he or nor anyone in the Vale of Shadows was responsible for the evil plaguing Kuldahar. It seems we will need to go back to Arundel and inform him of this. Perhaps he will have a clue as to what we should do next. ~
@417   = ~Ooooh!  Ooooh!  An elf!  Are you a Bladesinger?  Can you wield two weapons at the same time?  Can you dodge Fireballs and sleep upside-down in trees?  Ooooh!  Ooooh!  Tell me you can!~
@418   = ~So you came to Icewind Dale?  Elf, you're stupid.  This place is stupid too.~
@419   = ~Good luck with your travels.  It was nice talking to you, but I have to go.  Farewell.~
@420   = ~Yeah, yeah, yeah.  It's not fun.  I gotcha.  So... hear any good rumors lately?~
@421   = ~True, true.  Being a traveler, you must hear a lot of interesting things.  Have you heard anything interesting lately?~
@422   = ~Yeah, I suppose your right.  I have to be getting back to the "icy anvil" myself.  Farewell.~
@423   = ~Who you calling id-jut?!  I are saying fare-well.~
@424   = ~Yeah?  I'm an idiot?  Well... you're a little pointy-eared tree-hugger!  Elfy!  Ha!  Yeah!  How do you like THAT, Mister Elfy Elf-Face?  Farewell... elfy.~
@425   = ~Oh, so I'm an idiot, am I?  Why don't you step a little closer and say that?  Let's see what you're made of, pansy.~
@426   = ~Walk in darkness, "friend."  Farewell.~
@427   = ~That sounds stupid.  Elves are such dummies.~
@428   = ~Interesting.  Hear any good rumors on your way here?~
@429   = ~Do you know of any other adventurers in Easthaven?~
@430   = ~I wish you well on your travels.  Farewell.~
@431   = ~Hmm.  Thanks for the advice.  Have any other information to share?~
@432   = ~Yeah, whatever.  Anyone tries to pull one over on me and I'll take 'em out so quickly I'll be a LEGEND in these parts.  Move over heroes, there's a new shire-reeve in town.  I'm so fast I can practically dance on the tip of a sword.  WHOOSH!  WHOOSH!  Watch me go!~
@433   = ~I'll keep that in mind.  Farewell.~
@434   = ~Uh oh.  Farewell.~
@435   = ~Pray to your fruity gods, elfboy.  It's time for your head to "Retreat" from your body.~
@436   = ~Now that you mention it, something does seem out of place.  I can't quite put my finger on it, but... yes.  Something's been odd about the weather.  Be careful in your travels.  Farewell.~
@437   = ~Sorry we upset you Mr. Garbage Can.  We just want to ask you, is that your natural stench we smell or did you make a mess in your armor because our weapons scared you.~
@438   = ~Too bad, good bye.~
@439   = ~We apologize for our hasty words, can we start over again?~
@440   = ~Eh?  I haven't noticed anything.  Thanks for talking, though.  Farewell.~
@441   = ~Interesting.  Thanks for the advice.  Farewell.~
@442   = ~I'm not your friend, elfling.~
@443   = ~Greetings.  Have you heard any rumors in your travels?~
@444   = ~Well met, Erevain.  Just thought I'd greet you in passing.  Farewell.~
@445   = ~Uh... farewell.~
@446   = ~Interesting.  Have any information to share?~
@447   = ~There doesn't seem to be much adventure around here, friend.~
@448   = ~Thanks for the information.  Farewell, Erevain.~
@449   = ~Oh, thank the gods.  Whoever you are, you picked the perfect time to wander by.  I could really use some help. ~
@450   = ~The name's Apsel.  But, please... we don't have time for such pleasantries.  I need your help!~
@451   = ~A wolf somehow got into my workshop and is tearing the place apart.  It attacked me as I was opening the shop this morning.  I was so startled by the sight of the beast that I accidentally broke the key off in the lock while trying to get away.  Now I can't even get back in.~
@452   = ~I am a scrimshander.  I carve the huge, bony skulls of knucklehead trout into fine works of art.  This summer, southlanders will come up and buy my pieces to take back to their fancy shops -- that is, of course, if I ever get any work done.  Damn wolf!~
@453   = ~I'd be most grateful if you could go in there and get rid of that stupid thing for me.  Then I could get back to my scrimshaw.  Of course, you'll have to find a way to get the door open first.~
@454   = ~I ought to spin your head for talking to me that way.  Ah, forget it.  You're not worth it.  I'll take my troubles elsewhere.~
@455   = ~Be'land~
@456   = ~I sincerely thank you.  The door to my shop is just around the corner here.  Please get rid of that demonic canine as soon as possible.~
@457   = ~All right, you greedy bastard, I'll throw in some gold for your trouble.  Will that satisfy your copper-clenching black heart?~
@458   = ~You again.  Look, I'm begging you...  help me get rid of this wolf?  Please?  The creature is in there right now, ravaging my workshop as we speak.~
@459   = ~What in Tempus's holy name are you still puttering about here for?  I can still hear that wolf jumping around in there.  If you don't hurry, there won't be anything left of my shop.  I'll be ruined!~
@460   = ~Ah!  My friend!  The wolf is no more!  I am now a happy man.  Thank you for helping me.  Here's a little something for your trouble.~
@461   = ~Hello again, my friend.  Thank you again for helping me with my problem.~
@462   = ~Please... help me, please.~
@463   = ~You again.  Look, I'm begging you...  help me get rid of this wolf?  Please?  The creature is in there right now, ravaging my workshop as we speak.~
@464   = ~I don't care!  Break it down if you have to.  I doubt it'll come to that, though.  Judging by the looks of you, I'd say you've picked more than your share of locks.  My door shouldn't be much of a challenge. ~
