@1219  = ~I'll live.  What is this place?~
@1220  = ~Back off.  I'll be doing the question-asking around here.  First question... what are you doing down here?~
@1221  = ~I really need to be going.  Farewell.~
@1222  = ~My name is Albion.  I am the Exalted Keeper of this Eldathyn retreat.  I am sorry if I startled you.  My students and I would never have expected... how did you make it down here?~
@1223  = ~Eldath?  The goddess of nature's peace, eh?  Why do you have a temple in this god-forsaken place?~
@1224  = ~You and your students have just been sitting down here under a tribe of lizard men, a few packs of trolls and a legion of undead?  How'd you pull that off?~
@1225  = ~Do you know anything about the Heartstone Gem?~
@1226  = ~How did I make it down here?  Pure talent.  Do you know anything about the evil forces gathering in this area?  ~
@1227  = ~I'm sorry, I must be going now.  Farewell.~
@1228  = ~Oh my!  I will have some of the priests tend to your wounds.  Please accept our hospitality until you feel well.  How did you find your way down here?~
@1229  = ~I came here looking for an item from Kuldahar Pass.  It is called the Heartstone Gem.  Do you know of it?~
@1230  = ~I am looking for a source of great evil in Icewind Dale.  Do you know anything about the recent incursion of dark forces into this region?~
@1231  = ~I am a mercenary.  My feet take me wherever there is profit to be made.~
@1232  = ~This is a sanctuary for Eldathyn.  We were drawn here when we dreamed of the foul pollution that was occurring in this area.   Unfortunately, the trolls, lizard men, and other creatures are very difficult to work around.~
@1233  = ~Why don't you just kill them?~
@1234  = ~Do you know anything about the Heartstone Gem from Kuldahar?~
@1235  = ~Why are you showing concern?  Your black aura is clearly visible.  The robes of a priest of the goddess of peace cannot hide your true form from a paladin.~
@1236  = ~I... what?  We're Eldathyn.  We worship the goddess of peace and tranquility.  She is a goddess of nature.  As her servants, we are charged with protecting the purity of water and the life it gives.~
@1237  = ~Uh-huh.  I'm investigating the recent appearance of evil forces in the Kuldahar Pass and Vale of Shadows.  Do you know anything about what's going on?~
@1238  = ~Tell me what you know about the Heartstone Gem.~
@1239  = ~Very well.  If you have need of our beds, you may rest here.  Our healer, Sharra, is located to the east.  May Eldath and her peace watch over you.~
@1240  = ~Our non-violent nature protects us from the raw aggression of our... less intelligent cousins.  The lizard men and trolls leave us alone as long as we don't venture too far into the caves above.~
@1241  = ~Interesting.  Do you know anything about the Heartstone Gem?~
@1242  = ~I'm trying to locate the source of evil in Kuldahar.  People have been abducted and monsters are wandering in the pass, killing locals and passersby.  Do you know anything about this?~
@1243  = ~The Heartstone Gem?  It's a sacred artifact of Silvanus, isn't it?  I heard that it used to rest in Kuldahar, but that it was lost long ago.  Other than that, I don't know much about it.~
@1244  = ~What of the great evil that has been stirring in this area?  Do you know what is causing it?~
@1245  = ~I must be going now.  Farewell, priest.~
@1246  = ~Evil, you say?  I believe you were right to come to the Dragon's Eye.  There must be some evil force at work to have brought the trolls and lizard men here.  If you want my opinion, I think it's that foul priestess of Talona in the caves above.~
@1247  = ~Yes.  I encountered her minions.  Do you think that she is involved with the theft of the Heartstone Gem?~
@1248  = ~I must be going now.  Farewell, priest.~
