@1781  = ~I don't care much for your tone... or your choice of words. Do you have some sort of problem with halflings?~
@1782  = ~Hardly a recommendation. I take it you don't care for this halfling much.~
@1783  = ~Oh, Aldwin and I came to an... arrangement. I think gold is the least of his worries.~
@1784  = ~It's nothing to do with him being half a man - if so, then most of Kuldahar would be guilty. It's his manner; that ill-mannered excuse for a gunny sack came into ownership of that inn recently, and it's a queer thing *how* he did, too. ~
@1785  = ~How so?~
@1786  = ~~
