@2613  = ~I come with the authority of Kuldahar to seek out the source of the evil that has fallen upon this land.~
@2614  = ~It matters not. I need to investigate this tomb. Will you allow it?~
@2615  = ~Ah, I see... And who in Kuldahar holds the deeds to this vale or this tomb? By what right do they send you here with *authority* to kill, loot, and destroy?~
@2616  = ~It is the right of any people to take action against a perceived threat.~
@2617  = ~It matters not who sent me here. I need to investigate this tomb. Will you allow it?~
@2618  = ~Perceived threat? What are you talking about? These guardians have been here for centuries and have harmed no one! Where is your threat?~
@2619  = ~Fear~
@2620  = ~I am curious, Mytos. Why does a *tomb* need this much protection? Unless, of course, it is more than it seems?~
@2621  = ~~
@2622  = ~Bah! You speak rubbish now. You are trying to justify your wanton acts by creating threats where they do not exist. ~
@2623  = ~You are not answering my question. Why does a tomb need this much protection?~
@2624  = ~Cause Serious Wounds~
@2625  = ~Then allow me to investigate this tomb fully, Mytos.~
@2626  = ~For no other reason than the fact that the protection was available. As one of the faithful the person interred here had access to Bone Dancers. So he used them. Nothing sinister is going on.~
@2627  = ~~
@2628  = ~Disintegrate~
@2629  = ~I don't understand. What is a bone dancer?~
@2630  = ~No. It is forbidden. As a matter of fact I have spent too much time talking with you and neglecting my duty. I must demand that you surrender the keys in your possession and leave here. I will not ask again.~
@2631  = ~I have no intention of leaving until I am satisfied there is no threat to Kuldahar within these walls.~
@2632  = ~Mytos, I am trying to be reasonable here. I cannot in good conscience leave until I have investigated this tomb fully. Can we come to some understanding?~
@2633  = ~Then you leave me no choice. Guardians. Slay this fool!~
@2634  = ~~
@2635  = ~I have no idea. What happens outside this vale is of no concern to me.~
@2636  = ~Why should I believe you innocent of Kuldahar's woes?~
@2637  = ~A Bone Dancer, such as myself, is a servant of Myrkul. It is our duty to raise guardian dead to protect places of importance to the faith. It is I who raised the guardians of this tomb.~
@2638  = ~I see. I would ask you to allow me to investigate this tomb fully, Mytos.~
@2639  = ~No. You may not leave here until you have surrendered the keys you have in your possession.~
@2640  = ~I cannot do that at this time.~
@2641  = ~First I must investigate this tomb. Will you allow this?~
@2642  = ~No, we cannot. You have your duty and I have mine. This conflict was inevitable... Guardians. To arms!~
@2643  = ~So be it.~
@2644  = ~Adequately? Are trying to imply that you could have done better? I think not.~
@2645  = ~Your creations could not prevent our entry here, Mytos. If they are a reflection of your abilities as a necromancer, then you need more practice in the art.~
@2646  = ~Forgive me. I meant no insult to you, Mytos. ~
@2647  = ~Summon Shadow~
@2648  = ~With str ref~
@2649  = ~Proceed... no further, traveler, as... I  would... speak with you.~
