@2721  = ~I think I'll be on my way. Farewell.~
@2722  = ~Yeah, of course we got space for such fine upstanding travelers such as yourself. Rest up - you got a big day of being quiet tomorrow, "friend." I hope that's not a *problem* for you.~
@2723  = ~You keep making sure the rooms are free, and we won't have ANY problems, Aldwin. ~
@2724  = ~Not at all... but I'm not tired at the moment. I'll return.~
@2725  = ~Yeah, of course we got space for such fine upstanding travelers such as yourself. By the way, I talked it over with the other folks in town like you asked, and they're willing to let the whole Eidan thing slide -- as long as I take a percentage out of my profits to help the town. Damn warm-blooded vampires. ~
@2726  = ~Good. I'd like to rest, then.  ~
@2727  = ~The road to a clean conscience can be a long one, Aldwin. I'll return to check on you later. ~
@2728  = ~I'm Aldwin, and maybe having your head way up there don't make you hear so good -- do you want a *room* or not? My inn's the only inn in town, so don't even be thinking you'll find a better deal anywhere else.~
@2729  = ~~
@2730  = ~My head may be up here, half-man, but my fist'll be happy to swing down and pay you a visit if need be.~
