@5079  = ~Are you all right?  You seem preoccupied. ~
@5080  = ~I'm surprised you saw me as deep into day-dreaming as you seem to be.  Your time might be better spent fishing in the lake than in your dreams. ~
@5081  = ~Sorry for disturbing you.  I'll take my leave. ~
@5082  = ~Hmmm... eh?  Oh, greetings to you again.  Forget something last time we spoke?~
@5083  = ~[no text]~
@5084  = ~Jhonen, I think I found the reason for those dreams you're having.  ~
@5085  = ~Well, I was curious:  are you all right?  You seem preoccupied...  even more so than when we last talked.~
@5086  = ~You're one to speak of forgetfulness, considering how deep into day-dreams you seem to be.  Your time might be better spent fishing in the lake than in your dreams. ~
@5087  = ~No, not at all.  Sorry for disturbing you.  Farewell.~
@5088  = ~No, no, I'm fine - just taking in the view of the lake for a bit, trying to shake these dreams out of my head... the lake's beautiful, isn't it?  ~
@5089  = ~Ah, it is indeed.  Many a song has been written about light upon a lake's mirror.  It's like looking into the sky, isn't it?~
@5090  = ~Dreams?  Usually those fade upon waking, friend.  Mayhap a day's worth of fishing will chase them away. ~
@5091  = ~I must take my leave.  Farewell. ~
@5092  = ~Well, perhaps so, but my luck's not been what it has been in the past.  I head farther out, but there's no fish to be found.  Even my dreams have been troubled by it.  ~
@5093  = ~What kind of dreams?~
@5094  = ~~
@5095  = ~Aye, you've hit on the head, you have!  Songs, you say?  Odd you should mention that; I've heard many a song in my dreams - mayhap it's part of a snippet I heard once before.  Would you know of it if I were to hum a few bars?~
@5096  = ~I may... my repertoire is somewhat limited, but go ahead.~
@5097  = ~As long as you don't mangle the tune too badly, I might.  Just be sure to stop when I tell you to. ~
@5098  = ~It's kind of a hmmmnnn... srnnnn... srnnnn... ha-nnnnn... and then - it's... it's like -- damn, I can't quite get it!  And I hear it so clearly in my dreams, too; the tune's like crystal. ~
@5099  = ~No, no, I think I recognize the general tone.  It's definitely not a human verse, though - the "srrnnn-srnnn" tempo there is more like ocean waves and currents - like sea elves, or sirens.  And you say you've been having strange dreams, too?  Hmmmm.  Tell me about them. ~
@5100  = ~Ah, well, the dreams have been fishing in *me* of late, friend.  So much so I can barely catch a wink before they rouse me from it.  A frustration it is at times; sometimes, it seems like they're more real than the waking world. ~
@5101  = ~~
@5102  = ~~
@5103  = ~Well, there's a woman... and don't give me that eye, it's not like you think... she walks upon the surface of the lake as if it were flagstones instead of waves.  She doesn't say anything, just sings - beautiful songs, but I can't understand a word.  ~
@5104  = ~Some races that dwell beneath the sea, including the elves, don't speak as we do.  Perhaps the woman is speaking to you.  And speaking through dreams would not be beyond their talents. ~
@5105  = ~The woman in your dreams is a sea spirit, Jhonen.  Her kind speak through song, which is why you couldn't understand her.~
@5106  = ~Well, if dreams are your only worry, Jhonen, your life can't be too bad.  Dreams should be a comfort, not a curse. ~
@5107  = ~~
@5108  = ~If truth be told, friend, I... th... dammit, there's no sense to it!  These dreams are eating at me like a starving wolf!  I can barely hold a daily thought in my head before the memory of the dreams hounds its way back in there.  I... by the hells, I don't know how much more of this I can take.~
@5109  = ~~
@5110  = ~If I can find some way to help you, Jhonen, I will.  I don't know how I can, but I'll see what I can find out.~
@5111  = ~~
@5112  = ~Eh?  You're not playing on a man's hopes, are you?  I'd be grateful for just *one* night of peace. ~
@5113  = ~~
@5114  = ~I'll see what I can do.  If I think of anything, I will return.~
@5115  = ~A... sea spirit?  Eh... what does she *want,* then?  Why the *dreams?*~
@5116  = ~She's one of the spirits of the lake that seek to lure men to their deaths, Jhonen - the dreams are "bait," if you will.  If you would be cursed with these dreams no longer, you must give up your worldly possessions and leave this town at once.  You can give your possessions to me, if you wish.  I will see that they're, uh, disposed of. ~
@5117  = ~Her name is Elisia.  Speaking through dreams is one of the talents of her race - she speaks to you because she loved one of your ancestors and has carried a promise for him for many, many years.  ~
@5118  = ~Uh, she wanted me to give you a gift, but I seem to have misplaced it.  If I find it, I shall return.~
@5119  = ~Delthyr~
@5120  = ~One of my *ancestors?*  Why come to me, then?~
@5121  = ~Your features remind her of him, and your heart is as strong, if not stronger.  She has come to love you, but she cannot let you see her in the flesh.  She wishes to give you something that belonged to your ancestor, if you would take it.~
@5122  = ~I was fearing it was such a thing - the song in my dreams was too beautiful to be anything else but trouble!  My father raised no fool, and he told me never to try and fight the spirits that lurk in the North.  I'll hate to leave this place, but it seems I have no choice.  At least I don't have much in the way of belongings... here, take these.  Farewell... and thanks, friend.  ~
@5123  = ~Ah, some fish and a fisherman's knife.  I'll be sure these are disposed of... properly.  Now, if I were you, I'd hurry and leave, without speaking to anyone about this.  Farewell, Jhonen. ~
@5124  = ~Aye, I will.  Of course I will... sorry, it's... well, it's a bit much to be laid upon a fisherman all at once.  I... well, I'd be honored to accept anything she wishes me to have.~
@5125  = ~Here you are, then.  It's the blade your ancestor used against Icasaracht, the last of the white dragon matriarchs.  It lay within the dragon's heart for almost a century at the bottom of the waters.  Carry it well and know that Elisia loves you; your dreams shall trouble you no more. ~
@5126  = ~By the Spine of the World... even shattered, this blade's a wonder.  But... no more dreams, you said?  I... well, I'll miss them, actually.  Her songs... beautiful.  Simply beautiful.~
@5127  = ~I'll tell her, Jhonen.  Farewell.   ~
@5128  = ~I'm on my way.  Nothing but the clothes on my back to take me to the next town. ~
@5129  = ~Good.  Just be sure *not* to speak of what occurred - the dreams may come again if you do.~
@5130  = ~Thanks again, friend.  It's like the dream dust was wiped from eyes.  I can't thank you enough for all you've done. ~
@5131  = ~It was no trouble, Jhonen.  Glad I could help. ~
@5132  = ~That song -- are you the woman that Jhonen sees in his dreams?~
