@6289  = ~You win some, you lose some.~
@6290  = ~I apologize for the casualties incurred.  At least you're safe.~
@6291  = ~Your brother?  Where is he?~
@6292  = ~Your brother?  Where is he?~
@6293  = ~Silas didn't make it.  The largest yeti I've ever seen tore out of the snow and took a piece out of him with its claws.  He fell, dead as a stone, blood everywhere.  There... there was nothing I could do.  He was carrying our family heirloom... but it's lost to us now. ~
@6294  = ~We told Jhonen about dispatching the sea spirit by the shore.  He should be able to sleep easier now.~
@6295  = ~Not if I butcher that large yeti that killed your brother.  But that wouldn't be an easy... or cheap... task.~
@6296  = ~Hmm.  I can try and recover that heirloom for you.  Can you tell me how to get to the Vale? ~
@6297  = ~If you would be willing to go into the Vale and find the heirloom, I'd pay you for your trouble. ~
@6298  = ~I'll do it, then.  Tell me how to get to the Vale of Shadows. ~
@6299  = ~We were taking the main path, but considering how many beasts were in the Vale, Arundel may know a safer path you can take.  He wanders the mountains quite a bit and knows of more hidden trails than there are branches on the great oak.  His home is southwest of the great tree; it's the two-story house made out of stone. ~
@6300  = ~I already spoke to Arundel.  I'll be on my way to the Vale soon. ~
@6301  = ~We were able to retrieve Mirek of Kuldahar's family heirloom.~
@6302  = ~Arundel?  I'll see him before I go, then. ~
@6303  = ~Thank you.  Now that Silas is gone, that heirloom is all I have left to remember my family by.  I would appreciate its safe return.  Also, if you come across any more yetis, you might want to collect their pelts once you've done away with the beasts.  Conlan, the blacksmith here in town, buys the pelts for a fair price.~
