By means of a Ray of Enfeeblement, a wizard weakens an opponent, reducing its Strength and thereby the attacks that rely upon it.  The victim is reduced to a strength of 5 for the duration of the spell, unless a save vs. spell is made.  This spell does not affect combat bonuses due to magical items, and those conferring increased Strength function normally.  However the target receives all of the penalties for a 5 Strength, such as attack and damage penalties, as well as lower weight allowance.~
@7727  = ~~
@7728  = ~~
@7729  = ~What about the balance?  Surely you must see that what happens to the people of Kuldahar will affect you as well.~
@7730  = ~But... you live in Kuldahar.  How can you not care what happens to the town and its people?~
@7731  = ~I see.  You don't give a damn about anyone but yourself.  You'd rather sit locked up in this tower with your nose buried in these dusty old books.~
@7732  = ~I understand you're busy, but could you at least offer some assistance in the way of spells or scrolls.  I'd be willing to pay, of course.~
@7733  = ~Very well.  Then I shall disturb you no further.  Farewell.~
@7734  = ~What is so important about your work?~
@7735  = ~~
@7736  = ~When we charmed the Harbormaster, he told us that there were quite a few Iron Throne merchant ships coming into port these past few weeks.  He thinks they were bringing in iron.~
