Saving Throw: None
This spell warps the surrounding rock, reshaping the terrain into spiked projections that blend into the background. Any creature entering the area takes 2d4 hit points of piercing damage per round and must make a save vs. spell or have its movement rate reduced by 30%.
~
@8041  = ~What importance does razorvine extract serve?~
@8042  = ~Actually, I think I'll pass.  I'm rather busy right now.  Goodbye.~
@8043  = ~Well, to begin with, it won't grow within the Prime Material Plane, so it's extremely hard to come by.  There are countless magical proper... why am I even explaining this to you?  If you can find my apprentice and help him back here I will provide you with the information you need, and get you on your way.~
@8044  = ~Periapt of Proof Against Poison~
@8045  = ~I'll see what I can do.~
@8046  = ~I can find your apprentice, for a price.~
@8047  = ~I'm not ready to take on any tasks at the moment, but I would like some more information from you.~
@8048  = ~Off with you then, and don't disturb me again until you've found him.~
@8049  = ~I'm on my way.~
@8050  = ~If my offer of information to the whereabouts of the entrance to an ancient, treasure-laden crypt is not sufficient, I'm confident another adventurer will be along shortly to offer his hand.~
@8051  = ~Alright, alright, I'll try and find him.~
@8052  = ~Probably so.  Goodbye.~
@8053  = ~The extract, but not the apprentice... most disturbing, the container for this.  I suppose I shall have to find another boy wet behind the ears.~
@8054  = ~And my information?~
