@8664  = ~Anyhow, I managed to get the ship airborne and was making excellent progress over the mountains.  It really was a magnificent view!  The billowing clouds, the snow-capped peaks that shimmered like diamonds in the sunlight...  I guess I was so enamored by the beauty of it all that I didn't notice that outcropping of rock until it was too late.~
@8665  = ~You hit the mountain?  What happened next?~
@8666  = ~~
@8667  = ~Well, the collision ripped the bottom of the ship wide open.  The steering mechanism was badly damaged and the ship began to lose altitude.  I tried desperately to keep it aloft, but down we came, falling from the sky like a stone.  It is by sheer luck that I crashed here in the town of Kuldahar.~
