@9735  = ~So you have returned, heathen.  The garments you wear weigh down not only your bodies, but your souls.  Let us wrap your bodies in hair shirts, saturated with scarlet tears.  This will liberate your souls from the terrible burden of our world.~
@9736  = ~My... my god.  I know not who you are, but you have delivered us from such a terrible nightmare...  I dreamt that I was swimming in pitch under a blood red moon.  So much suffering have I caused.  So much suffering must I endure to repay the debt of sin I have incurred.~
@9737  = ~Who are you?~
@9738  = ~[no text]~
@9739  = ~[no text]~
@9740  = ~I am Perdiem, once a faithful priest of Ilmater.  I used to watch over a monastery of faithful priests and priestesses outside of Illefarn.  One day, a man came to the monastery.  He said his name was Poquelin, and that he had come to help us find the true faith of Ilmater.~
@9741  = ~There was something about his eyes, his voice, that hypnotized us.  His voice was so commanding, so powerful, that we were swept up in his sermons with a disturbing passion... it frightened us, but we could not help but fall deeper into his web of deception.~
@9742  = ~We abandoned dozens of sick and dying worshippers in the halls of our monastery.  We went north, through the Kuldahar Pass.  Many died, but at that point, we no longer cared.  All was done for the glory of Ilmater, for the propagation of the faith.~
@9743  = ~Even as Poquelin became more fascist, more militant, we could do nothing to resist.  Poquelin's idol had us enthralled.  Those who resisted were drained of life and turned into the zombies who guarded this black temple.  ~
@9744  = ~Spell Failed: Indoors~
@9745  = ~It used to be a temple to Berronar Truesilver, though you'd never recognize it now.  I have not only committed blasphemy against my god, but against a proud mother goddess of the dwarves.  I owe a great debt to many gods and people.  Thank you for liberating my soul.~
@9746  = ~Animate Dead (Necromancy) 
Level: 3
Sphere: Necromantic
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 8 hours
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 
This spell creates the lowest of the undead monsters, skeletons or zombies, usually from the bones or bodies of dead humans, demihumans, or humanoids.  The spell causes these remains to become animated and obey the simple verbal commands of the caster.  The undead remain animated until they are destroyed in combat or are turned; they cannot be dispelled.  The caster can animate one skeleton or one zombie for each experience level he has attained.~
@9747  = ~No problem, friend.  You can start repaying your debt by healing me.~
@9748  = ~You're welcome.  Can you heal us?~
@9749  = ~It is true.  You have caused much pain and death in your madness.  The path to recovery will be a long one, but our fight continues.  What can you tell us about Poquelin?~
@9750  = ~[no text]~
@9751  = ~Sure.  What do you know about Poquelin?~
@9752  = ~Poquelin is no priest of Ilmater.  He is a sorcerer of some sort.  There is something cold and unnatural about his eyes.  His skin, his hair... everything about him rings false.  The way he walks, the way he holds himself... it is as though he is a stranger in his own body.~
@9753  = ~Interesting.  Could you heal me?~
@9754  = ~~
@9755  = ~My... my god.  You have delivered us from such a terrible nightmare...  I dreamt that I was swimming in pitch under a blood red moon.  So much suffering have I caused.  So much suffering must I endure to repay the debt of sin I have incurred.  I am sorry that I sought to cause you harm.~
@9756  = ~How did all of this happen?~
@9757  = ~I bow before you in thanks, my friends.  Although I am unworthy to truly consider myself to be your equal, I ask if there is anything I can do to help you.~
@9758  = ~~
@9759  = ~Can you heal me?~
