@9813  = ~Farewell.~
@9814  = ~Okay, mate.  Think I'll do just that.~
@9815  = ~So you return.  What do you want of me?~
@9816  = ~I do not serve the giants.~
@9817  = ~Nothing.  Farewell.~
@9818  = ~You asked me to free you from slavery.  I will make an effort to do so, although I foresee this as a difficult task.~
@9819  = ~~
@9820  = ~I have been working toward earning you your freedom.~
@9821  = ~You asked me to kill the creature that the slaves are being sacrificed to.  I will do it.~
@9822  = ~Hey kid, the world is full of disillusionments, live with it. ~
@9823  = ~You're right, don't worry, we'll stop her.~
@9824  = ~~
@9825  = ~I have been working toward slaying the beast that the slaves are being sacrificed to.~
@9826  = ~~
@9827  = ~I find that hard to believe... but let us suppose for the moment that it is true.  What is it that you want of me?~
@9828  = ~~
@9829  = ~Then ask them.~
@9830  = ~~
@9831  = ~Do you know anything about these caverns?~
@9832  = ~Is there anything you can tell me about the giants?~
@9833  = ~That skeleton over there.  I find it fascinating.  Do you know anything about it?~
@9834  = ~~
@9835  = ~My name is Davin Berenson.  I am at your service.  Is there something else you would ask of me?~
@9836  = ~Yes, I have more questions.~
@9837  = ~No, farewell.~
@9838  = ~I am a slave.  As a matter of fact, all the people that you see here are slaves.  However, we will not be slaves for much longer.~
@9839  = ~Why do you say that?~
@9840  = ~Every day the giants come here and take one of us away.  Whoever is taken is never seen again.  Our numbers are dwindling so it is only a matter of time before we are slaves no more.~
@9841  = ~What happens to the ones who are taken away?~
@9842  = ~They are sacrificed to some... creature that lives here in the caverns.  I know this because the giants gloat over our fate as they lead their chosen victim off.~
@9843  = ~The creature you speak of is dead.  There will be no more sacrifices.~
@9844  = ~That is a terrible fate that none should suffer.  I would end it if it were in my power.~
@9845  = ~Oh? How do you know this to be true?~
@9846  = ~I am the slayer of the creature. ~
@9847  = ~That is excellent news.  You have saved us from a horrible fate.  However, we are still in a desperate situation since the giants hold us captive here.  I would ask that you free us.~
@9848  = ~Yes, I will make an effort to do so.  I foresee this as a difficult task, though.~
@9849  = ~No, I have no desire to fight the frost giants.  Farewell for now.~
@9850  = ~I will consider it.  Farewell for now.~
@9851  = ~Yes... but I think I know how it may be accomplished...~
@9852  = ~This is hell.  Urdlen and his Worm Realm have nothing on Marketh's mines.~
@9853  = ~Oh?  Please tell me.~
@9854  = ~Move along, stranger.  You'll only find death down here.~
@9855  = ~There are only two paths out of here.  One lies through the heart of the giants' domain, and they know we cannot pass through without being seen.  The other is a small cave to the north of here.  The giants only place one guard upon us to prevent us from entering that cave and gaining our freedom.~
@9856  = ~apply~
@9857  = ~Herschel~
@9858  = ~Herschel~
@9859  = ~You picked the wrong place to poke your nose.  Get out of here before Marketh and his goons find you.~
@9860  = ~Kaella~
@9861  = ~Kaella~
@9862  = ~Alan Blackblade~
@9863  = ~Alan Blackblade~
@9864  = ~Do you know what lies within this cave?~
@9865  = ~Another day, another ton of gemstones dumped in the lap of a madman.~
@9866  = ~I used to like mining, you know...~
@9867  = ~Well... no.  Perhaps you should start your quest by scouting the cave and removing any... *hazards* there before removing the guard.~
@9868  = ~It's said that some of our people escaped from Dorn's and are safe somewhere.  Tarnelm in the Oubliette may know more.~
@9869  = ~Very well.  I shall do so.  Farewell.~
@9870  = ~[no text]~
@9871  = ~The mad mage allied with Marketh has bull-headed men and umber hulks serving him.  When we fail, the hulks rip us to pieces.~
@9872  = ~I have done so already.  You need fear nothing in the cave.~
@9873  = ~Entillis Fulsom~
@9874  = ~Entillis Fulsom~
@9875  = ~Elementals are being destroyed nearby.  I can feel the ground cry out when the earth elementals are harmed.~
@9876  = ~No!  No!  Don't hit me!  The crossed hands, the bloody wrists!  No more!~
@9877  = ~Stay away from the Artisan's District and Malavon's Dome.  Shikata's salamanders are kind compared to the monsters there.~
