@15182 = ~Uhhhh... Greetings, adventurers... Pardon me while I gather my thoughts.  Who are you, and what has just come to pass?  ~ [LARR_10]
@15183 = ~We are adventurers who have come to the Severed Hand to seek your knowledge and power.  In doing so, we learned of the curse bestowed here and your sanity lost centuries ago.  We have restored you to some of your former self and beseech you for aid.~
@15184 = ~To further our journeys, we came to the Severed Hand to find that in order to continue, we had to restore you to some semblance of your former state.  Now we ask that you return the favor and divine what we need from the Heartstone.~
@15185 = ~This is the only answer you need:  We have restored you, and we have the power to destroy you as well.  We need you to unlock the power of the Heartstone.  We care nothing for this pathetic excuse of a hovel that you cursed by your own arrogance.~
@15186 = ~[NULL NODE]~
@15187 = ~Indeed you have, noble adventurers.  It must have taken great courage and strength to make it as far as you did, let alone restore some balance to my thoughts.  I am eternally in your debt.  But surely you did not come to the Hand of the Seldarine on a whim?  Tell me what it is you seek.~ [LARR_12]
@15188 = ~I seek knowledge that only can be divined through the Heartstone.~
@15189 = ~I wish to know more of the events that came to pass here in the Hand.~
@15190 = ~Hmmm.  To the point, I see.  Very well.  At least you speak honestly.  Your deeds will be repaid.  What do you wish?~ [LARR_13]
@15191 = ~We seek to use the divination powers of the Heartstone. ~
@15192 = ~First, tell me what happened to you and the Hand.~
@15193 = ~I was mistaken to think you adventurers were here for reasons other than personal gain.  I will not make that same mistake again.  Tell me what you want and be quick about it.   I will only tolerate so much from orc dung.~ [LARR_14]
@15194 = ~You stand corrected.  You will give us the power we need from the Heartstone.~
@15195 = ~You will relate to us the events that lead to the destruction of the Hand.~
@15196 = ~You are mistaken.  Orc dung would show more mercy than us.  Prepare to die once again, Larrel.~
@15197 = ~Very well.  As legend states, the Heartstone Gem is an ancient artifact from a time long forgotten.  Its most notable owners were the druids of Kuldahar before one within their circle stole the gem.  It was thought forever lost, until now...~ [LARR_15]
@15198 = ~The Heartstone Gem contains powerful scrying abilities that can divine the affairs of people throughout the Realms.  There are only a few within the land who know how to release its powers.  I am one of them.  ~ [LARR_16]
@15199 = ~With that said, what is it you seek to learn from the Heartstone Gem?~ [LARR_17]
@15200 = ~We seek to learn source of the evil that troubles the North.~
@15201 = ~Trouble has reared its ugly head.  We seek its source so that we may crush it!~
@15202 = ~We've been hired to look into some problems that have been plaguing the North.~
@15203 = ~Then you will have what you seek.  Hand me the Heartstone Gem.~ [LARR_18]
@15204 = ~Here you are.~
@15205 = ~You wish to learn what came to pass within the Hand of the Seldarine?  Very well.  There is much to tell.  Shall I start with the time of prosperity, the betrayal, or our darkest hour? ~ [LARR_19]
