@15457 = ~So, at last you have come, *editor.*  Know that the price of intruding into my domain is that you write only good things about Icewind Dale.~
@15458 = ~Wh -- what are you talking about?~
@15459 = ~Don't attempt to deceive me.  I am Kresselack, the Black Wolf.  I have slaughtered many editors and their families.  Occasionally, I have gone so far as to slaughter their friends.  And pets.  Does this disturb you?~
@15460 = ~Not really.  It's just that after killing all your undead minions I expected a little more than vague threats directed against the person playing this game.  ~
@15461 = ~They are not vague threats!  Do you doubt my power?!~
@15462 = ~Look, "Kresselack the Black Whatever you are," here's how things stand: one more threat outta you, and I'm switching off this computer.  You'll be left ALL alone.  In the dark.  With the dead.  Understand?~
@15463 = ~Sigh.  Well, they told me to be threatening.  At least tell them I tried.  I'm not allowed to say any more except that this is the end of the Preview Version of Icewind Dale.  And to thank you for playing.  So... thank you.  Oh, and write a good review.~
@15464 = ~That better not have been a threat.~
@15465 = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal~
@15466 = ~No!  No, it wasn't... uh, sir.  Or ma'am.  It's hard to tell what your player looks like from here.  Please -- enjoy the game.~
@15467 = ~Frost~
@15468 = ~I'm off to write my preview, then.  Farewell.~
@15469 = ~We spoke with Denaini in Solonor Tower of the Severed Hand about the other priests.  She told of us of their horrid existence and has asked us to put them to proper rest.~
@15470 = ~One of the villagers in destroyed Easthaven, Jhonen, told me the rest of the villagers are being held in a stockade in the southeast section of town.  He said the high priest of the town, Everard, was among them and that Everard might know a way into the huge tower of ice. ~
@15471 = ~We returned to Kuldahar - only to find someone masquerading as Arundel.  The shapechanger, whoever he was, thanked us for disposing of Yxunomei and allowing him "free reign" over Kuldahar and Easthaven.  He vanished before we could learn more.  I fear that with Arundel's murder, darker times are ahead for the people of Kuldahar and Easthaven. ~
@15472 = ~We met a ghost named Norlinor near an ancient dwarven forge.  Norlinor told us of Terikan, a lich that was attempting to unleash a horde of undead from the plane of Negative Energy into Dorn's Deep.  Norlinor told us that to destroy Terikan, we would need to obtain his soul container from the Hall of Heroes, and bring it into the tomb of Jamoth, also within the Hall of Heroes. ~
@15473 = ~Emerging from the frozen, goblin infested pass, we finally arrived in Kuldahar.  Nestled within the roots of a massive oak tree over several hundred feet tall, the small hamlet was a welcome sight after such a harrowing journey.~
@15474 = ~"To the dust with you, Prime!"~
@15475 = ~"No!  Back, stay back!  Get to your portal!"~
@15476 = ~"Die, pipsqueak!"~
@15477 = ~"Come!  Come to the hallowed temple of suffering!"~
@15478 = ~"The sins of the flesh must be purged!  Purged on an altar of fire!"~
@15479 = ~"With your blood and bones, we will build an empire of living pain!"~
@15480 = ~"...gauntlet, vambrace, couter, rerebrace, pauldron..."~
@15481 = ~"...tasset, greave, poleyn, sabaton..."~
@15482 = ~"...black..."~
@15483 = ~"Kill them!  Kill them all!"~
@15484 = ~Uh... I'm doing okay, I guess.~
@15485 = ~I'm not doing too well.~
@15486 = ~Drop the act, Poquelin.  I'm sick of all these charades.  I've been hacking through enemies for days, weeks, just to get out of these damned mountains.  I'm not about to let a crazed man in a bloody Ilmaterian high priest's robe stand in my way.~
@15487 = ~I am pleased to hear it.  So many young people today suffer needlessly.  ~ [POQU_02]
@15488 = ~They live through a dull pain, sublimely drifting under the waves, never understanding the ecstasy that awaits them if they open their hearts to Ilmater.~ [POQU_03]
@15489 = ~You're not fooling me, Poquelin.  I just came from the "temple of Ilmater" below - I don't think that Ilmater would be pleased with how you've chosen to worship him.~
@15490 = ~Corruptor of faith, twister of minds, your perversion of the Ilmaterian faith has come to an end.  I will see that you are brought to justice.~
@15491 = ~It saddens my heart to hear such news.  You seek solace, yes?  You seek the loving embrace of Ilmater?  ~ [POQU_04]
@15492 = ~All you seek, all you have ever sought, can be found through me and the glorious suffering of my god.~ [POQU_05]
@15493 = ~~
@15494 = ~Hmmm... I suppose you're right.  The whole "mockery of suffering" thing only amuses one for so long.  ~ [POQU_06]
@15495 = ~It seems that my campaign here has run its course.  It was time to move on, in any event.~ [POQU_07]
@15496 = ~Cut to the point, Poquelin.~
@15497 = ~Quit speaking in riddles, villain.~
@15498 = ~As interesting as I find your musing on various topics ranging from the nature of justice to the history of the world, I'd really appreciate it if you'd quit rambling.  Thanks.~
@15499 = ~Ah... justice.  But, what *is* justice?  No.  Don't answer.  That was a rhetorical question.  There are more important things you must answer for - such as your attack on my domain.~ [POQU_08]
@15500 = ~~
@15501 = ~~
@15502 = ~I'm sorry, but war and charades are the only two games I know how to play.  If they are not to your liking, I'm afraid you'll be ill-equipped to play the game that's about to begin.~ [POQU_09]
@15503 = ~~
@15504 = ~~
@15505 = ~~
@15506 = ~After centuries of Yxunomei's laboriously worded speeches and delusions of grandeur, it is a welcome change to hear such... succinct threats from an enemy. ~ [POQU_10]
@15507 = ~Thank you for disposing of her, by the way - her speeches were quite tiresome... and she suffered her defeats so poorly.~ [POQU_11]
@15508 = ~What are you up to, Poquelin?  Why the Spine of the World?~
@15509 = ~I think you'll know exactly how she feels in a minute, Poquelin.  Prepare yourself.~
@15510 = ~The only thing really standing in the way of my conquering this territory was Yxunomei.  When you killed her, you removed the largest obstacle in my campaign.  ~ [POQU_12]
@15511 = ~As you probably already know, my arrival in this world was a result of conflict with my ancient adversary.~ [POQU_13]
@15512 = ~I was exiled from my home plane when my vendetta with Yxunomei got... as my 'superiors' said... "out of control."  ~ [POQU_14]
@15513 = ~As soon as I arrived in this world, I knew that Yxunomei would follow.  After all, what's a few thousand years and a billion miles between old friends?~ [POQU_15]
@15514 = ~I sought out a base of operations from which I could start a military force.  In the process of doing so, I heard something calling to me from a distant glacier.  ~ [POQU_16]
@15515 = ~It was this... Crenshinibon.  It's an artifact so old that it makes me seem young, a crystal shard with magical powers of such magnitude that Kuldahar's Heartstone Gem looks like a child's toy.~ [POQU_17]
@15516 = ~Just having it in my possession caused the monstrous creatures of this land to leave their ancient homes and seek me out.  Its other powers are too numerous to mention.  ~ [POQU_18]
@15517 = ~Corgeig Axehand~
@15518 = ~Corgeig Axehand~
@15519 = ~Despite the fact that the shard has a somewhat... overbearing... personality, our plans seem to coincide.~ [POQU_19]
@15520 = ~As for my lieutenants, they were easy enough to find.  All of them were eager to join my cause, except for poor, naive Brother Perdiem.  ~ [POQU_20]
@15521 = ~The guise of an Ilmaterian Revered Brother was perfect for traveling and gathering information in Icewind Dale.  The form was easy enough to assume.  ~ [POQU_21]
@15522 = ~The information inside of Perdiem's head allowed me to... flesh out the role.~ [POQU_22]
@15523 = ~Everything was going well until that annoying Arundel and your good friend, the late Hrothgar, decided to investigate Yxunomei's poorly-veiled activities in Dragon's Eye.~ [POQU_23]
@15524 = ~If that idiot had been a little more clandestine in her business, no one would have suspected.~ [POQU_24]
@15525 = ~To stall Yxunomei and seal off Icewind Dale, I used Crenshinibon to freeze the passes... but not quickly enough to prevent Hrothgar's band from starting their expedition.  ~ [POQU_25]
@15526 = ~I had Kreg Frostbeard and his giants cause the avalanche that crushed Hrothgar, Accalia, and those other fools.~ [POQU_26]
@15527 = ~Thrown~
@15528 = ~After that, I didn't really care what you were doing... until you seized the Heartstone Gem from Yxunomei.  ~ [POQU_27]
@15529 = ~Melee~
@15530 = ~Lightning Bolt~
@15531 = ~Fireball~
@15532 = ~I thought that Arundel would be the only person capable of using it.  When I killed him, I thought the threat was ended.~ [POQU_28]
