@16727 = ~You told Arundel of your meeting with Kresselack. ~
@16728 = ~As a young man, I was a conqueror.  I ravaged the lands and brought all who opposed me under my rule.  I built a kingdom upon the corpses of my enemies, and I reveled in the glories of war.  ~ [KRES_06]
@16729 = ~However, in time my sword grew heavy, my aim less true, and I realized I was growing old.  For the first time in my life, I knew fear...~ [KRES_07]
@16730 = ~Realizing that death would some day claim me, I returned to my homeland.  For months I pondered what course I should pursue in my remaining years.~ [KRES_08]
@16731 = ~I thought of my kingdom and all that I had fought to create, but it was meaningless to me.  A kingdom lasts a lifetime, but death lasts an eternity.  ~ [KRES_09]
@16732 = ~I decided to forsake all that I had wrought in life for a place in the afterlife...~ [KRES_10]
@16733 = ~I ordered this tomb built in utmost secrecy and squandered the wealth of my kingdom doing so.  Upon its completion, I traveled here with my most faithful followers to survey the work.~ [KRES_11]
@16734 = ~Finding all in order, I slew the workers and buried them in the Vale outside.  My faithful followers I sacrificed to become... the guardians of this tomb.  ~ [KRES_12]
@16735 = ~Finally, I sacrificed myself to my god, hoping to stand at his side in the land of the dead.  Little did I know that my actions would instead bind me to these halls for eternity.~ [KRES_13]
@16736 = ~~
@16737 = ~~
@16738 = ~~
@16739 = ~~
@16740 = ~~
@16741 = ~I care not at all whether you believe me, adventurer.  I am centuries dead and bound to these halls for eternity.  ~ [KRES_16]
@16742 = ~I care even less for the living or their gathering places.  If your Kuldahar is beset by evil, it is not of my doing.  Go seek your villain elsewhere.~ [KRES_17]
@16743 = ~~
@16744 = ~~
@16745 = ~~
@16746 = ~Auril, the ice goddess, is worshiped by some here in the cold north.  Auril commands her followers to extinguish all fires, to open structures to the cold winds, and to deny warmth a place to gather.  ~ [KRES_19]
@16747 = ~As you can see, my tomb would be an abomination to a follower of Auril.~ [KRES_20]
@16748 = ~A priestess of Auril has stood at the threshold of my tomb and gazed within.  Recently she attempted entry, but my guardians foiled her.~ [KRES_21]
@16749 = ~Now that you have slain my guardians, there is nothing to prevent her from returning and carrying out the will of Auril.~ [KRES_22]
@16750 = ~I do not wish to spend eternity in a cold, lightless hell.  Find this Aurilite... and slay her.  Only then will I answer you.~ [KRES_23]
@16751 = ~~
@16752 = ~~
