@18232 = ~It was nothing, really.~
@18233 = ~You're lucky we happened to be nearby.  You really ought to keep that little brat on a shorter leash.~
@18234 = ~~
@18235 = ~You are too modest.  Now, what brings you to my home today?~
@18236 = ~~
@18237 = ~~
@18238 = ~~
@18239 = ~Sorry to disappoint you, but this is in fact my home.  I may be a fishmonger, but that doesn't mean I hawk fish like some street vendor.  I deal in large quantities of dried knucklehead and scrimshaw, the bulk of which I keep stored in my warehouse down on the shore.~
@18240 = ~~
@18241 = ~~
@18242 = ~~
@18243 = ~Yes... well, I keep telling him not to fish the far shores, but you know how impetuous boys can be.  In any case... what brings you to my home today?~
@18244 = ~~
@18245 = ~[no text]~
@18246 = ~~
@18247 = ~I can't tell you how glad I am to see you again.  I thought for sure we would end up as food for those one-eyed brutes sooner or later.  Watch yourself... there may still be more of them about town.~
@18248 = ~We'll keep an eye out for them.  Farewell.~
@18249 = ~Quick, we've got to go get Hrothgar!  There are monsters in town!  They almost ate me!~
@18250 = ~Whoa, slow down there.  What are you talking about?~
@18251 = ~Out of the way, boy.  We've business to attend to.~
@18252 = ~Monsters!  A whole bunch of them.  They came down to the shore while I was fishing.  I dropped everything and ran when I saw them, but they didn't chase me.  I thought they were going to eat me, but I guess they were just after my fish.~
@18253 = ~Where are these monsters now?~
@18254 = ~You best be telling the truth.  You know what happens to little boys who cry orc.~
@18255 = ~Go bother someone else with your tall tales.  We've no time for such nonsense.~
@18256 = ~Just over the bridge... down by the lake.  My da told me not to fish so far out by myself, but I can't help it.  That's where I catch the big ones.  He's gonna kill me when he finds out I've lost today's catch.  All because of those stupid monsters!~
@18257 = ~Don't worry... we'll deal with these thieving monsters.  In the mean time, take this knucklehead.  It'll keep you out of trouble with your da.~
@18258 = ~Don't worry... we'll deal with these thieving monsters and get you your fish back.~
@18259 = ~All right, we'll go check it out.  But if we find out you're lying to us, we'll send you to the bottom of the lake.  ~
@18260 = ~Tough luck, kid.  Maybe next time you'll listen to your old man.  Farewell.~
@18261 = ~It's the truth.  I swear!  They're ugly and mean with pointy teeth and green skin.  Go see for yourself!~
@18262 = ~Very well.  Where are these monsters of yours?~
@18263 = ~I think you've heard one too many bedtime stories.  Run along now.~
@18264 = ~Okay, but don't say I didn't warn you.  Those monsters looked hungry.  They'll probably eat you up just like they did my fish.~
@18265 = ~Monsters ate your fish?  What in the nine hells are you talking about?~
@18266 = ~We'll take our chances.  Farewell.~
@18267 = ~Thanks.  I'd best be getting home now.  My da's probably worrying about me.~
@18268 = ~"A dwarf dares to set foot here?"~
@18269 = ~"Have you come to push the dagger further into our backs?"~
@18270 = ~...~
@18271 = ~"Speak for yourself!"~
@18272 = ~"Do you deny the destruction wrought by your treacherous kind?"~
@18273 = ~You're back.  Were you able to get my fish back from those monsters?~
@18274 = ~Today is your lucky day, boy.  Here is your fish... at least what is left of it.~
@18275 = ~Boo~
@18276 = ~"I will not tolerate your filthy presence anymore!"~
@18277 = ~"Wretched thing."~
@18278 = ~As a matter of fact, we did.  But before we hand it over... how about a little something for our efforts?~
@18279 = ~Sorry, boy.  No luck yet.  Farewell.~
@18280 = ~But I don't have anything.  I'm very poor... that fish was all I had.  I was going to sell it to Pomab.  Knucklehead bones are worth a lot.  They use them for scrimshaw and stuff.~
@18281 = ~In that case, we'll keep the fish and sell it ourselves. ~
@18282 = ~Please, you're breaking my heart.  Here, take your precious fishbone.~
@18283 = ~Hey!  That's my fish!  You're no better than the monsters.  I'm telling my da.~
@18284 = ~Oh, all right.  Take the fish.  The damn thing stinks anyway.~
@18285 = ~You do that.  Farewell.~
@18286 = ~Well, if you do run into those monsters, try and get my fish back for me.  I'll be in big trouble with my da if I go home without any fish today.~
@18287 = ~Go away.  I don't want to talk to you.  You're mean.~
@18288 = ~Have it your way, you little brat.  Farewell.~
@18289 = ~Thank you again for getting my fish back.  I told my da all about you.~
@18290 = ~That's nice.  Farewell, Damien.~
@18291 = ~I'm scared.  Please don't let the big monsters eat me.~
@18292 = ~Don't worry.  You're going to be all right now.  I promise.~
@18293 = ~You know, I'm beginning to think you're obsessed with the idea of monsters eating you.~
@18294 = ~We'll try.  Farewell.~
@18295 = ~Huh?~
@18296 = ~Begin Game~
@18297 = ~Pick Pocket Succeeded -- Target Had Nothing to Steal~
@18298 = ~Thank the Gods you're here.  You best go over and speak with Everard.  The old warhorse has taken quite a beating, but he still has the strength enough to lead us to safety.~
@18299 = ~I shall speak with him straight away.  Farewell.~
@18300 = ~Something sinister is behind this attack... I can feel it in my bones.  Whoever or whatever it is, I'd be willing to wager what's left of my shop that it's inside that cursed ice tower.  Watch your backs, friends.~
@18301 = ~You do the same.  Farewell, Apsel.~
@18302 = ~Amazing.  I didn't think anyone could put down those brutes.  You should speak with Everard.  He'll be wanting to form a plan to save us all.~
@18303 = ~Thank you for saving us.  The last thing I wanted was to die in this miserable town.~
@18304 = ~I never thought I'd lay eyes on you again, dearie.  Quick, we've no time to waste.  Go talk to Everard.  He'll know what to do next.~
@18305 = ~Keep yourselves safe now, dearies.  We'll never forget what you've done for us here.~
@18306 = ~We've already been down into your cellar - we killed all the beetles we found down there.~
@18307 = ~"It worked!  It worked!"~
@18308 = ~"Blew it up I did!"~
@18309 = ~"hehehhahhaHAHA"~
@18310 = ~"Ascend not, they will"~
@18311 = ~"Spell now, I complete"~
@18312 = ~Gareth and the other slaves believed that their leader, Vera, was dead. We informed Gareth that she is alive and in hiding. The news pleased him and he will inform the other slaves.~
@18313 = ~We met a strange hermit in the valley at the mouth of Kuldahar Pass.  He claimed to have witnessed the avalanche that wiped out the rest of the expedition from Easthaven and nearly killed us as well.  He told us, somewhat reluctantly, that the town of Kuldahar lay to the east of the valley, just beyond an old mill.~
@18314 = ~The spirit of Kresselack asked us to slay an Aurilite priestess whom he thinks intends to destroy his tomb.  We have agreed to find this priestess and deal with her but not necessarily slay her. In any case, Kresselack says that he senses her presence within the Vale of Shadows.  We should begin our search there.~
@18315 = ~We met the "Lizard King" of Dragon's Eye.  He informed us that the upper caves of the volcano belonged to him.  We tried to leave, but he quickly attacked us, claiming that his people need food.~
@18316 = ~Orrick, the mage in Kuldahar, mentioned that he was searching for the ruins of a lost elven outpost rumored to be located somewhere in the mountains near Kuldahar Pass.  He seemed particularly interested in obtaining any knowledge that pertains to an ancient elven enchantment called a mythal.~
@18317 = ~Norlinor~
@18318 = ~Never mind who I am!  Tell me what you are doing in this tower or I'll cut your ears off and feed them to you.~
@18319 = ~~
@18320 = ~Please... I don't want to die.  Not here.  Not like this.  You've got to do something.  Ask Everard.  Yes, that's it.  He'll know what to do.~
@18321 = ~Thank you, stranger.  If you manage to get through this alive... you'll be welcome to stay at my Inn anytime -- free of charge.~
@18322 = ~Yes, they're dead.  Now hand over the coins.~
