@22414 = ~All right then, Hailee.  I will not make you go. ~
@22415 = ~Those games are for babies, and 'sides, there's no one here to play *with,* except Purvis, and he gets mad when you pitch pebbles at him!  ~
@22416 = ~There's *no* other children in town?~
@22417 = ~There's just me... father's always in the shop making his stupid barrels... and mother's always drinking in the inn... there's nothing to DO in this stupid town.  ~
@22418 = ~~
@22419 = ~Your troubles do not interest me.  Just watch who you tell tales to from now on.~
@22420 = ~I'm sorry to hear that, Hailee... but I must go.  Farewell.~
@22421 = ~Uh-huh, sometimes in the forest, too, but not much... mostly just in town.  By the well, sometimes, or Purvis' shack, or I climb up in the tree by the Inn... there's a really good view up there. ~
@22422 = ~A good view?  Of what? ~
@22423 = ~Purvis?~
@22424 = ~Purvis the grave-digger!  He hasn't said much since he got here, but father says he buries DEAD people.  When I climb the trees around here, I have a good view inside his house n' others.~
@22425 = ~What other things do you see up in the trees?~
@22426 = ~People in town.  Of the inside of the inn.  And... things.  Things I can't tell you about...  *secrets.*~
@22427 = ~Secrets?  Like what? ~
