@22479 = ~Well, take your chances if you want.  Now, let's hear your secret.  You promised. ~
@22480 = ~~
@22481 = ~Oh, it did!  It said, "Minstrel, please spare me the catch-basket, and I will teach you a song... a secret *magic* song."~
@22482 = ~A secret magic song?~
@22483 = ~"Oh yes, a secret magic song," the fish said. "I will sing it to you, but in order for the magic to work, you must sing this song to a special little girl up north, and she must keep it for her own."~
@22484 = ~Was the girl me?!  Was the fish talking about *me?!*~
@22485 = ~Indeed, and listen to the song: 

    Hailee, Hailee, skipping amongst the trees 
    Keeper of secrets, whispered in the leaves 
    A secret for a secret, speak of what she sees!~
@22486 = ~Is that *my* song?~
@22487 = ~Yes, Hailee.  It is your special song, and you may keep it forever and ever.  But you can only sing it when you're at home with your parents.~
@22488 = ~~
@22489 = ~I'm going to go catch as many talking fish as I can and make them give me more songs. ~
