@24399 = ~~
@24400 = ~I came upon the Seer an' survived the meeting... me eyes did not.  ~
@24401 = ~~
@24402 = ~She caught me wandering the Gloomfrost, an' when I saw her, it was like I'd been frozen -- an' I watched the last sight o' me life as her dagger plucked out me eyes. ~
@24403 = ~Why did she do that?~
@24404 = ~She feared I'd go tell the rest o' me Clan that I'd seen her in the Gloomfrost.  She didn't want me bringing any o' me brothers here -- or anyone else. ~
@24405 = ~We'll see that she answers for her crime.~
@24406 = ~What were you doing in the Gloomfrost in the first place?~
@24407 = ~~
@24408 = ~Is this dented shield yours?~
@24409 = ~Do you have any supplies, Tiernon?~
@24410 = ~Do you have any more supplies we might buy from you?~
@24411 = ~A sad tale.  Farewell, Tiernon.~
@24412 = ~~
@24413 = ~Ye'll do no such thing.  The matter's laid to rest between me an' her, an' it's none o' yer business.  Ye leave avenging to me when *I* feel it necessary, hear?~
@24414 = ~~
@24415 = ~~
@24416 = ~Very well.  Is this dented shield yours?~
@24417 = ~~
@24418 = ~~
@24419 = ~As you wish.  Farewell, Tiernon.~
@24420 = ~~
@24421 = ~Ah, now, finally *there's* the question I was expecting.  By asking, ye've told me more than ye know.  ~
@24422 = ~What do you mean?~
@24423 = ~~
@24424 = ~I can hear it in yer voice - ye've never felt the *call.*  Me people, the dwarves, we have a special kinship with the forge. ~
@24425 = ~I can hear it in yer voice - ye've never felt the *call.*  As ye well know, our people have a special kinship with the forge. ~
@24426 = ~There comes a time in our life when we feel the forge's pull, an' we are guided to craft an item o' such quality, such strength, that it takes a part of ourselves.  ~
@24427 = ~The price is we will never forge another thing greater - it is the way of our people.~
@24428 = ~Is this why you're here?  This doesn't look like a good place to mine for metal. ~
@24429 = ~And the call of the forge led you to the Gloomfrost?~
@24430 = ~I must take my leave.  Farewell, Tiernon.~
@24431 = ~~
@24432 = ~I never felt the call of iron or steel or mithril or silver -- all these things sleep beneath the earth, but in the Gloomfrost, I found the material I was to forge... ice.  ~
@24433 = ~Why would you forge ice into a weapon?~
@24434 = ~And that will give it power?  Ice seems too fragile. ~
@24435 = ~Ice - it is water, sky, stone, all in one.  It will be like forging the howling wind, the cold o' winter, an' the sky itself into a weapon.  ~
@24436 = ~Can ye feel the chill?  It's the ice o' the Gloomfrost, askin' to be worked, *needing* to be worked, slowly, carefully, with pick an' chisel, with a slow flame an' a craftsman's blade.~
@24437 = ~An' so that's why I came here - bringing me forge an' all me tools.  ~
@24438 = ~What did you make?~
@24439 = ~So you shape weapons from ice...  can you make a rose?~
@24440 = ~Is this dented shield yours?~
