@24545 = ~Eh... now, Denthelm isn't a name I'm fond of, stranger.  Just Tiernon will do.  ~
@24546 = ~Denthelm's nothing to be ashamed of.  How were you to know the returning enchantment you inscribed on the throwing hammer worked unless you tr--~
@24547 = ~At the risk o' echoing meself, stranger, just *Tiernon* will do. ~
@24548 = ~But what happened to you?  Your weapons are practically legendary... but your own people don't even know where you vanished to.~
@24549 = ~~
@24550 = ~Aye, me business here is me own, stranger.  But ye've found me, ye have.  If ye want, ye can tell the fellows down in the Sunset Mountains I'm well an' good, making trouble as always.  Now who are ye an' what do ye want?~
@24551 = ~~
@24552 = ~~
@24553 = ~Aye, ye've found me, ye have.  If ye want, ye can tell the fellows down in the Sunset Mountains I'm well an' good, making trouble as always.  ~
@24554 = ~I'll let them know should I be traveling that way.  They'll be pleased to hear you're still alive.~
@24555 = ~I can't tell it by sight - let me hold it... heh.  I'd almost forgotten about this little piece.  The enchantment's nearly fallen asleep, though... let me see if I can wake it up...~
@24556 = ~All right.~
@24557 = ~There ye are... it's breathing steady as a winter's snow now.  Shouldn't be any more trouble. ~
@24558 = ~All right, then.  I'll put it to the test soon enough.~
@24559 = ~I'll put it to the test soon enough, then.~
@24560 = ~Wait.  Ye have something else o' mine, ye do.  That sword ye're carrying, the one that looks like it's been dredged from Dinneshere.  Where did ye come by it?~
@24561 = ~Aihonen's Blade?  I got it from a fisherman in Easthaven. ~
