@24564 = ~Aye, long ago I may have -- for some poor fool that thought he'd take all o' Faerun on his shoulders.  Pah!  That damn thing's singing is making me ears bleed!  Hand it over!~
@24565 = ~Uh, all right.~
@24566 = ~Damnable metal... wail curses at *me,* will ye?!  I'll fix ye!  Not me fault yer master was a thrice-damned fool, not me fault he died... now, hold still, damn blade...~
@24567 = ~Tiernon, what are you d--?~
@24568 = ~Ye be quiet!  Give me a moment...~
@24569 = ~Last time I give a blade a woman's temperament - there, the lass is all better now, just needed a little comforting hand to smooth out the rough edges.  Keep her close, an' she'll watch out for ye. ~
@24570 = ~Thanks, Tiernon.  I'll wield this blade with honor. ~
@24571 = ~That's what I'm afraid of, stranger - that's what the last one who held her did.  Best ye be gone, now.~
@24572 = ~~
@24573 = ~~
@24574 = ~Farewell then, Tiernon.~
@24575 = ~Aye, perhaps I could... Why would ye want such a thing?~
@24576 = ~My reasons are my own, dwarf.  Can you make it or not?~
@24577 = ~I know of a man who spent his life in search of one... and it ruined him.  Perhaps it is not too late for him to find it, and his life, again. ~
@24578 = ~Hmm.  It'd be difficult... but a challenge, an' I'll not duck a challenge.  Hand me the small block of ice from the bench, an' let yer eyes guide me hands...~
@24579 = ~~
