@24608 = ~[Resolved.]Death comes with swift wings.  My hiding place... is a place of hiding no longer.~ [SEER001]
@24609 = ~Silence, witch.  We have killed your beasts, now we have come for you. ~
@24610 = ~We know of what you did to Tiernon - we are here to see you harm no one else.~
@24611 = ~Hiding?  Why are you hiding here?  ~
@24612 = ~Your eyes... what happened to them?~
@24613 = ~Ah... the shaper of ice, the child of the elder races.  [Saddened]My fear whispered to me when he first came to these caves.  'Blind him,' it said.  My spirit was weak, so fear ruled my actions.~ [SEER002]
@24614 = ~[Confessing.]I took from him his eyes, for I feared he would tell others of my hiding place.  [Pause.]He has forgiven me... but the weakness of my spirit I cannot forgive. ~ [SEER003]
@24615 = ~He may have forgiven you, but you will receive no mercy from me.  Prepare yourself, witch. ~
@24616 = ~Very well.  Why are you hiding here?  ~
@24617 = ~Your eyes... did you tear those out as well?~
@24618 = ~[Was expecting this, not surprised, even in the face of violence.]So the crossing of our paths is upon us... I have seen this moment take place from a distance of many years, and I saw you would bring the spirits of violence with you. ~ [SEER004]
@24619 = ~You knew we were coming?~
@24620 = ~[Slightly amused by the question]Why am I hiding?  [Chiding.]Come... why does anyone hide?  ~ [SEER005]
@24621 = ~[Shifts gears dramatically, suddenly deadly serious.]*Death* is what I hide from.  My spirit fears for its life as do the spirits of all living things... so much that I must run from death, cheat it by hiding from it. ~ [SEER006]
@24622 = ~[Doesn't realize what the player's talking about.]My eyes?  [Gets it.]Ah, my eyes... they served me too well. ~ [SEER007]
@24623 = ~~
@24624 = ~An axe can be of the strongest steel, and so sharp it cleaves the man that wields it.  A fire can burn so fiercely it scars a child that seeks its warmth.  ~ [SEER008]
@24625 = ~And eyes can be blessed to see so far that a woman may see the end of her own life. ~ [SEER009]
@24626 = ~In seeing my own death... it turned my eyes to dust.  Yet still... I see.  Many things, past and present, here and elsewhere... your coming... and my death, both linked like chains.  ~ [SEER010]
@24627 = ~Your coming is why I buried myself here, for in visions, my death walks in your shadow.  It is for that that I fled my people, tried to hide myself from your eyes, and the reason I have long feared this meeting...~ [SEER011]
@24628 = ~[Tired, resolved to die.]Yet fear tires the spirit, and it has brought me little except more fear.  [Dismissive, doesn't care.]Kill me if you wish... or leave me here and *she* will kill me.  In the end, I die the same death.~ [SEER012]
@24629 = ~"She will find me?"  Who are you speaking of?~
@24630 = ~This "she" - is she the one you are hiding from?~
@24631 = ~[Almost 'tut-tutting' the player.]You have seen the creature that wears Wylfdene's body like a cloak.  She has chosen wisely, that one.~ [SEER013]
@24632 = ~Do you mean Jerrod?  Wylfdene told us he had merged with Jerrod's spirit.~
@24633 = ~Wylfdene is possessed?  By what?~
@24634 = ~No, no, Jerrod is long dead and gone from this world... this creature is of a different sort, a spirit of things that once were but can never be again.~ [SEER014]
@24635 = ~Who is this creature?~
@24636 = ~She is the spirit of one who died in the North long ago, and she carries the death of the North with her now.  She has taken Wylfdene's body, and with it, the heart of his people. ~ [SEER015]
@24637 = ~She is clever, and moves as ice moves, slowly and patiently.  She will prove a difficult foe, for she carries death with her... as do you all. ~ [SEER016]
@24638 = ~So how can we defeat this creature... this thing that's become Wylfdene?~
@24639 = ~If you know how we can kill her, witch, then *tell* us. ~
@24640 = ~All things have a weakness... and in this, the creature that is Wylfdene and I share a common one... Sight.~ [SEER017]
@24641 = ~[Turns promised answer into a question.]Do you know *why* I have hidden here, chosen *this* place? ~ [SEER018]
@24642 = ~The ice is a shield, more powerful than steel or iron.  Though it does not know this, the creature that is Wylfdene cannot approach it and remain Wylfdene. ~ [SEER019]
@24643 = ~~
@24644 = ~Speak plainly, witch.  I have little time to trade riddles with you.~
@24645 = ~Ice... is a curious thing.  One may see through it, yet see themselves *in* it.  Therein lies *power.*~ [SEER020]
@24646 = ~The creature that is Wylfdene is a proud thing, like all of her kind.  She cannot bear to see herself as anything other than she is, no matter what corpse she hides in.~ [SEER021]
@24647 = ~The mirror you held to enter here will force her to *see.*  In seeing, Wylfdene's body will melt from her like water...  No more Wylfdene, only the beast, the great wyrm of ice and snow. ~ [SEER022]
@24648 = ~Bring the ice mirror before her.  She will remember it, for it is of her, and a thing knows it own nature.~ [SEER023]
@24649 = ~But you can see what Wylfdene is... and what he isn't.  If you came with us, the barbarians would heed your word, and there would be no need for the mirror.~
@24650 = ~We have tracked you down through these filthy caves, and now you tell us to take a trinket before Wylfdene to end a war?  Better instead that you come with us and lend weight to our position.~
@24651 = ~In her shadow is my death.  I will not approach her.  The mirror is enough, and my words shall be heard only by you.~ [SEER024]
@24652 = ~If your Sight is true, then death will come for you whether you hide within these caves or not. ~
@24653 = ~~
@24654 = ~How can you be sure the mirror will expose her?~
@24655 = ~~
@24656 = ~Very well... if you will not come with us, then the mirror shall have to do.  I will take it to Wylfdene.~
@24657 = ~You speak truth... yet my path is mine.  Reason and fear are not brothers, and while I yet live, I shall not run to face my death *this* day or any other.~ [SEER025]
@24658 = ~So you will allow your enemy to choose the time of your death, rather than face it on your own terms?  Fear has truly claimed you.~
@24659 = ~So you will allow your enemy to choose the time of your death, rather than face it on your own terms?  Fear has truly claimed you... just as fear claimed you when you blinded Tiernon.~
@24660 = ~~
@24661 = ~~
@24662 = ~~
@24663 = ~[Hissing, Furious, for the argument has struck home]Enough!  Do you think your words *new* to me?  Do you think them *clever?* ~ [SEER026]
@24664 = ~They are neither!  I have heard you say them a hundred times in visions of this meeting, so be silent!  [Gathers composure]I have given you the weapon to stop this creature that has claimed Wylfdene - use it or not, I care little.~ [SEER027]
@24665 = ~~
@24666 = ~~
@24667 = ~[Chiding.]Child, you have been blessed with womanhood, with the cradle that creates two hearts where once was one.  You know the truth; you must, inside, where it matters.~ [SEER028]
@24668 = ~[Important plot point]A woman knows a woman's heart, and a strange, beautiful, and cruel thing it is.  But the cruelest of all is a heart of winter, for it beats not with love, but with loss, and *nothing* may comfort it.  ~ [SEER029]
@24669 = ~[Saddened]When a human heart breaks, it may heal and forgive.  When a heart of winter breaks, it is like ice... it shatters and can never be made whole again.  ~ [SEER030]
@24670 = ~A heart of winter is what will damn our people and yours, all so it may remember what life *once* was... not as it is.~ [SEER031]
@24671 = ~Why does this... creature that's possessed Wylfdene... why does she want to destroy the Ten-Towns?~
@24672 = ~We have heard enough.  We will take the mirror to Wylfdene and see the truth of your words.~
@24673 = ~Her heart was broken once by a man of the Ten-Towns.  A *mighty* breaking it was, for in it, she lost her kingdom, her love, and her life.  Now, her heart beats with the vengeance of winter.~ [SEER032]
@24674 = ~Surely she can be reasoned with.  There is no need for war...~
@24675 = ~Then her heart shall be broken again.  We will take the mirror to her, and we will bring this matter to an end.~
@24676 = ~[Cold, matter-of-fact]A woman's fury is a terrible thing.~ [SEER033]
@24677 = ~Many women have you met in your travels, many more have you *yet* to meet - you will learn their hearts. ~ [SEER034]
@24678 = ~In each, there is rage, and love, and hate, and sorrow.  I have seen all their deaths, whether death has come for them or not.  Shall I speak their hearts? ~ [SEER035]
@24679 = ~I would hear of what you see.~
@24680 = ~~
@24681 = ~One woman clutches a heart like a drowning man clutches a stone and knows not that it drags her down.  Her dreams are watchfires, signaling to her of war and victory that can never be.  ~ [SEER036]
@24682 = ~One dwells beneath a mirror of the sky and has a heart like an ocean, too big for her will to contain.  She once knew love, then loved again, and her love is what has damned the North.  ~ [SEER037]
@24683 = ~Another woman builds great ships upon molten seas, all the while dreaming of beasts of purity and how they might be corrupted... as she once was.  I see her die, and her dreams become ash. ~ [SEER038]
@24684 = ~And the last... oh, the last.  The elder races... their passions burn so *brightly* when fueled with justice and hope. ~ [SEER039]
@24685 = ~[Feeling pained by the tragedy.]One, but a child, loved so much she abandoned her own father to die beneath the earth for a people she had never met.  ~ [SEER040]
@24686 = ~All these things - they will come to pass... or already have.  You will meet them, or you have met them, it is of no matter.  Time cares nothing for now and then. ~ [SEER041]
@24687 = ~How do you know these things... do they come to you in visions? ~
@24688 = ~~
@24689 = ~I see as if through the eyes of hundreds, child... such sights... it is as if my life is split upon countless branches of a great tree, and I can see through the eyes of each branch into another place... another time.~ [SEER042]
@24690 = ~I have seen visions of the past, of death, of spiraling cities and a black-brambled garden, of creatures both spirit and stone.  In all these things... I was not myself... yet always I see through a woman's eyes.~ [SEER043]
@24691 = ~~
@24692 = ~If you would leave this place, I may speed your journey... though only to the entrance of the Gloomfrost, no farther.  Do you wish it?~ [SEER044]
@24693 = ~Yes, transport me to the surface.~
@24694 = ~Before I go, I would visit Tiernon one last time - can you take me to him?~
@24695 = ~No, I still have unfinished business within these caverns.~
@24696 = ~On your way, then - the moment of my death approaches.  It is best you not remain.~ [SEER045]
@24697 = ~Your death does indeed approach... by my hand.  Prepare yourself, witch. ~
@24698 = ~~
@24699 = ~[No idea why players are back.]Why have you returned?  We have said all that was needed, and now our paths must part.~ [SEER046]
@24700 = ~What do I do with the mirror again?~
@24701 = ~Can you transport me to the surface of the glacier?~
@24702 = ~~
@24703 = ~Then I shall take my leave.~
@24704 = ~Take it to the creature that is Wylfdene... now that you know the power of ice, you know how it may be used, and all shall be revealed. ~ [SEER047]
@24705 = ~~
@24706 = ~~
@24707 = ~I shall bring the mirror to Wylfdene, then.~
@24708 = ~Ah, sight is painful, is it not, spirit?  Such pain is well known to me. ~ [SEER048]
@24709 = ~And seeing yourself as you truly are - the most painful thing of all.  Look into the mirror, creature that is Wylfdene.  See truth... See yourself.  ~ [SEER049]
@24710 = ~[Final, steady.]It is done.~ [SEER050]
@24711 = ~Lay still, Seer - your wound is great, yet we may still save you.~
@24712 = ~You were foolish to come here without telling us, witch.  Had we known, we could have stayed Wylfdene's hand.~
@24713 = ~This wound is by time's hand; there is no healing it.  The time of my death is now upon me. ~ [SEER051]
@24714 = ~You were brave to come, Seer.  I thought your fear of death ruled you, and you would not help us face Wylfdene.~
@24715 = ~~
@24716 = ~You might have chosen to come earlier, witch.  With your presence, this matter might have been resolved quicker... and without your death.~
@24717 = ~~
@24718 = ~I have found that fear, the fear of death, is no small thing to put aside. ~ [SEER052]
@24719 = ~Yet I will not allow the hopes of my people and yours to be slain because of an old woman's fear.  Death comes for us all, and I for one, see it... and now, embrace it.~ [SEER053]
@24720 = ~~
@24721 = ~~
@24722 = ~You spoke truth to me back in the Gloomfrost, about my fear claiming me... I could not allow the hopes of my people and yours to be slain because of it.  Death comes for all, and I for one, see it... and now, embrace it.~ [SEER055]
