@25081 = ~You have questions for the spirits, yes?  Hasten your mouths with queries, for we thirst to return to our own.~
@25082 = ~Waylane~
@25083 = ~Waylane~
@25084 = ~What can the spirits tell me of the heroes of Easthaven?~
@25085 = ~Tell me about the missing caravan.~
@25086 = ~Brelm~
@25087 = ~Brelm~
@25088 = ~Gereth~
@25089 = ~Gereth~
@25090 = ~What plagues Jhonen?~
@25091 = ~What can the spirits tell me of Pomab?~
@25092 = ~Which way lies our fortune?~
@25093 = ~What do you see in the future for Easthaven?~
@25094 = ~I have no questions for you, spirits.~
@25095 = ~We count many dead among those whom Hrothgar has slain.  All are also counted among the wicked and unruly.  He and his associate, Everard, are true to their convictions.~
@25096 = ~Lucy~
@25097 = ~Accalia is a strong woman, devout and opinionated.  Hildreth is a dwarf through and through.  Erevain is quick to anger.  They are all strong warriors.  That is all the spirits can say.~
@25098 = ~The caravan is gone.  Man-beasts plucked the wealth like a plum from a tree and carried it to a cave.  They guard it with bow and axe.  That is all the spirits know.~
@25099 = ~Jhonen is lost in a sea of his ancestor's elven love.  She is trying to give him a tool to fight evil.  Its power may give rise to blacker waters.  The spirits know no else.~
@25100 = ~Pomab's blood runs with the fire of his ancestors, a weak flame that devours all it crawls across.  The querant would be wise to watch the snake in the snow.  The spirits are deaf to all other knowledge.~
@25101 = ~The querant's fortune lies in the Spine of the World with Hrothgar.  The querant must crack those stone bones to get to the heart of the matter.  All else is blood and ruin, so say the spirits.~
@25102 = ~The spirits see red blood on white snow and blue ice.  All else is clouded to our perception.  We leave you to ponder these things.~
@25103 = ~OUR MISERY CANNOT BE ABATED!  CALL OUT YOUR DAMNED QUESTIONS AND BE DONE!  THIS DAY, THE SPIRITS BURN FOR *YOU!*~
@25104 = ~Who caused the avalanche that killed Hrothgar?~
@25105 = ~What's happening in the Vale of Shadows?~
@25106 = ~What can the spirits tell me of Arundel?~
@25107 = ~What can the spirits tell me of Lysan?~
@25108 = ~What has become of Conlan's son?~
@25109 = ~What is the source of evil in the Vale of Shadows?~
@25110 = ~Where are the missing priests of Ilmater?~
@25111 = ~~
@25112 = ~There is a skylight in the roof of this tower that allows light into this hole. Presumably, there is something in the basement that requires direct sunlight.~
@25113 = ~ALL IS BLACK!  OUR SIGHT CANNOT PENETRATE ITS VEIL.  SEEK MORE POWERFUL COUNSEL THAN OUR TORMENTED SOULS!~
@25114 = ~ALL IS AS IT HAS BEEN, THOUGH ONE SEEKS TO END THE MASTER'S ETERNAL SLEEP!  SHE IS PART OF SOME GREATER SCHEME!  WE LEAVE YOU NOW!~
@25115 = ~HE AND THE GREAT TREE ARE KIN.  POWERFUL IS HE, THOUGH IN GREAT DANGER.  TORMENT US NO LONGER!~
@25116 = ~SHE IS MORE THAN SHE SEEMS.  HER BLOOD RUNS WITH ICE, AND HER VOICE IS FILLED WITH WINTER'S WIND!  THIS IS ALL WE CAN SAY!~
@25117 = ~HIS HEART BEATS STILL.  HE AWAITS HIS FATE IN A PLACE OF WARMTH AND STONE.  ASK US NO MORE!  THE PAIN IS TOO GREAT!~
@25118 = ~MYRKUL IS THE SOURCE OF EVIL, THOUGH NOT THE EVIL YOU SEEK.  THAT EVIL STRIVES TO DESTROY THE EVIL OF THE VALE.  ASK NO MORE!~
@25119 = ~IN A PLACE OF GREAT WARMTH AND DECAY, SHE HONORS HER GOD.  THE REST IS BLACKNESS.~
@25120 = ~The dead see.  Begin.~
@25121 = ~What attacked the Temple of the Forgotten God?~
@25122 = ~What has become of Conlan's son?~
@25123 = ~Where are the missing priests of Ilmater?~
@25124 = ~Which way lies our fate?~
@25125 = ~I seek powerful magic.  Where may I find it?~
@25126 = ~Who created the undead lieutenants?~
@25127 = ~Tell me of Albion and the Eldathyn.~
@25128 = ~Who is the odd little girl?~
@25129 = ~I have no questions for you at this time.~
@25130 = ~The dead see many trolls, many serpentine creatures, evil priests, wizards, and a host of undead.  They are lead by a singular power.~
@25131 = ~He lies in the belly of the rock of dying flame.  He is guarded by eight-legged fiends and scaled men.  Kill their king and slay the boy's guardians.  Then he will be free.~
@25132 = ~The martyr let herself be captured by the oppressors.  She is surrounded by poisonous clerics.  There are no other missing priests.~
@25133 = ~Down, into a bed of steam and rock.  Kill the queen of the serpents.  She is fiercely guarded.  She holds the key.~
@25134 = ~There is magic guarded by the king of the lizards.  Two corpses also hold weapons of great power.  Seize them, and the trolls will fall easily to your attacks.~
@25135 = ~In the throat of the dragon, turn south, and seek the eight swords.  Under her, find the elven body.  Below, turn east.  Follow the trail of black bugs to the dead man's goods.~
@25136 = ~Presio, a priestess of contagion.  She and the frost maid conspired to create them.   The dead behind the lieutenants hold the powers of both Talona and Auril.~
@25137 = ~Scales shift beneath their skin, and their blood runs cold.  Seek out clues to expose them.  Beware the mage and the High Summoner.  Free the captured heroes and keep death from your hearts.~
@25138 = ~She is a matron of war, with a form more terrifying than the one you have seen.  She is heavily guarded by traps, priests, and powerful warriors.  Use your most powerful weapons against her.  Abstain from flame, as she was born from such matter.  The water that burns, it is your salvation.~
