@25201 = ~BERSERKER: This warrior can achieve an ecstatic state of mind during combat that enables him to fight longer, harder and more savagely than anyone else.  This state of battle rage can sometimes make him as much a threat to allies as to enemies.

Advantages:
* every time opponent is hit, 20% chance of entering berserker state
* berserker state lasts 45 seconds, gives temporary +15 HP, +3 to hit and +3 damage

Disadvantages:
* while berserk, 20% chance every 6 seconds that player loses control of the berserker
* when control lost, berserker will always attack nearest person, friend or foe~
@25202 = ~three containers on the second level, various items on a spirit and in a wall in the northwestern quadrant of the third level, a container on a dividing wall in the west of the third level,   ~
@25203 = ~WIZARD SLAYER: This warrior has been specially trained by his sect to excel in hunting and attacking spellcasters of all kinds.

Advantages:
* for each hit on opponent, 10% cumulative spell failure penalty is applied.
* 1% magic resistance per level

Disadvantages:
* may not use any magic items except for swords and armor~
@25204 = ~KENSAI: This class is also known as the 'sword saint', and consists of a warrior who has been specially trained to be one with his sword.  They are deadly and fast and trained to fight without encumbrance.

Advantages:
* bonus +1 to hit and +1 damage for every 3 levels
* -2 to AC
* bonus -1 to speed factor for every 4 levels
* may use 'kai' ability one time per day for every 4 levels: this ability lasts 10 seconds and makes all attacks do maximum damage.

Disadvantages:
* may not use missile weapons
* may not wear armor~
@25205 = ~Murtlen~
@25206 = ~CAVALIER: This class represents the most common picture of the knight...the gentleman warrior who epitomizes honor, courage and loyalty.

Advantages:
* bonus +1 to hit with all large swords and blunt weapons per 5 levels
* may cast 'remove fear' 1 time per day per level
* immune to fear and morale failure

Disadvantages:
* may not use missile weapons~
@25207 = ~INQUISITOR: The Inquisitor has dedicated his life to finding and eliminating practictioners of evil magic and defeating the forces of darkness, and his god has provided him with special abilities towards that end.

Advantages:
* may use 'dispel magic' ability once per day per 4 levels: ability is used at speed factor 1 and acts at twice his actual level.
* may cast 'true sight' once per day per 4 levels
* immune to hold and charm spells

Disadvantages:
* may not use 'lay on hands' ability
* may not cast priest spells
* may not turn undead
* may not use 'cure disease' ability~
@25208 = ~UNDEAD HUNTER: This holy avenger has honed his abilities towards the destruction of the undead and other unnatural creatures, and is immune to many of thier more devastating abilities.

Advantages:
* +3 to hit and +3 damage vs. undead
* immune to hold
* immune to level drain

Disadvantages:
* may not use 'lay on hands' ability~
@25209 = ~FERALAN: This ranger has been raised in the wilderness by animals, cut off from civilization, and combines the savagery of a beast with the intellect of a man.  The Feralan may act like a man, but for the most part he acts like a wild animal.

Advantages:
* may use 'enrage' ability once per day per 4 levels
* while enraged: +2 to hit, +2 damage, -2 AC

Disadvantages:
* may not cast spells~
@25210 = ~down the third level stairs to the second level in a southeastern container, down the second level stairs to the first level in two containers to the east and north,~
@25211 = ~STALKER: Stalkers serve as covert intelligence-gatherers, comfortable in both wilderness and urban settings.  They are the spies, informants and interrogators...and their mastery of stealth makes them deadly opponents.

Advantages:
* +20% to stealth ability
* may backstab for a lesser amount than the thief class (level 1-8: x1, level 9-16: x2, level 17+: x3)

Disadvantages:
* may not wear armor greater than studded leather~
@25212 = ~BEAST MASTER: This ranger is a wanderer, not comfortable in civilized lands, who maintains a natural affinity for animals.  They are his friends and comrades-in-arms, and the beast master has a limited form of telepathic communication with them.

Advantages:
* +5% to stealth ability
* may cast a special version of the 'find familiar' spell.  This summons, randomly, either a cave bear, dire wolf or tiger.

Disadvantages:
* may not use metal weapons (such as swords, halberds, hammers or morning stars).~
@25213 = ~ASSASSIN: This is a killer trained in discreet and efficient murder, thriving on anonymity and surprise to perform his task.

Advantages:
* may coat weapon in poison once per day per 4 levels.  The next hit with that weapon will inject the poison into the target, dealing out 6 damage every 6 seconds for 30 seconds.  A saving throw vs. poison limits damage to 6 total.
* bonus +1 to hit and +1 damage

Disadvantages:
* only 15% per level to distribute on abilities~
@25214 = ~in possession of spirit, appellation "Lehland," fourth level, five containers on level four, two containers on level two of Solonor Tower, east and west of platform, three containers on level three of Solonor Tower,~
@25215 = ~BOUNTY HUNTER: This is a hunter of men, skilled in tracking down his quarry and bringing them back alive...whether this be for the lawful authorities or his underworld masters.  Bounty Hunters are specially trained at their task and make fearsome opponents.

Advantages:
* may activate special attack once per day per 3 levels: lasts for 18 seconds and all hits by the Bounty Hunter cause a cumulative 10% spell-casting failure penalty and a -1 to target's Strength.

Disadvantages:
* gets only 15% to distribute on abilities each level~
@25216 = ~SWASHBUCKLER: This rogue is part acrobat, part swordsman and part wit...the epitome of charm and grace.

Advantages:
* -2 to AC
* attacks move up at same rate as the fighter class, although the swashbuckler cannot specialize

Disadvantages:
* no backstab multiplier~
@25217 = ~BLADE: The Blade is an expert fighter and adventurer whose bardic acting abilities go towards making him appear more intimidating and fearsome.  His fighting style is showy but also quite deadly.

Advantages:
* +1 to hit and +2 damage with melee weapons 
* may use 'offensive spin' and 'defensive spin' abilities once per day per 4 levels
* offensive spin: lasts 24 seconds, gives an extra attack per round.
* defensive spin: lasts 24 seconds, roots him to the spot but gives -1 AC per 2 levels of experience.

Disadvantages:
* only has one-half normal lore value
* only has one-half pick pockets percentage~
@25218 = ~in possession of spirit, appellation "Kaylessa," first level of Sheverash Tower, one container in the northern half of the third level of Sheverash tower, one container in the eastern half of the fourth level of Sheverash tower,~
@25219 = ~JESTER: This bard uses his abilities to distract and confuse his enemies, cavorting madly during combat and being well-versed in the arts of ridicule and hilarity.  Do not confuse this opponent for a true fool, however, as he can also be quite deadly.

Advantages:
* jester's song does not help allies...instead it affects every opponent within 30 feet, and they must save vs. magic at +4 once per round or be confused.

Disadvantages:
* none~
@25220 = ~SKALD: This is a nordic bard who is also a warrior of great strength, skill and virtue.  His songs are inspiring sagas of battle and valor, and the skald devotes his life to those pursuits.

Advantages:
* +1 to hit and +1 damage with all weapons
* skald's song gives allies +2 to hit, +2 to damage and -2 to AC but does not affect fear or morale.

Disadvantages:
* pick pockets ability one-quarter normal~
@25221 = ~PRIEST OF TALOS: A follower of the evil god of storms, destruction and rebellion.  These clerics warn that Talos must be appeased or he will punish the land by destroying it.

Advantages:
* may cast 'lightning bolt' once per day per 5 levels
* may cast 'stormshield' once per day per 10 levels
* 'stormshield' spell lasts 6 seconds per level of the caster, protecting the caster from lightning, fire, cold and normal missiles

Disadvantages:
* none~
@25222 = ~PRIEST OF HELM: Followers of the neutral god of watchers and protectors are warriors in their own right and are often seen as defenders of the innocent.

Advantages:
* may cast 'true sight' once per day per 5 levels
* may cast 'seeking sword' once per day per 10 levels
* 'seeking sword' spell creates a spell in the priest's hand that cannot be dropped or unequipped...it gives 3 attacks per round at +4 to hit and 2-8 damage, lasting 1 round per level of the caster.  While equipped, the cleric may not cast spells.

Disadvantages:
* none
                          ~
@25223 = ~PRIEST OF LATHANDER: Followers of the good god of renewal, creativity and youth are very popular throughout the realm.  Lathander is celebrated nearly everywhere and has very wealthy temples devoted to Him.

Advantages:
* may cast 'hold undead' once per day per 5 levels
* may cast 'boon of lathander' once per day per 10 levels
* 'boon of lathander' spell lasts 6 seconds per level of the caster, giving the caster +1 to hit, +1 damage, +1 to all saving throws and 1 extra attack per round

Disadvantages:
* none~
@25224 = ~TOTEMIC DRUID: This druid closely identifies with a particular animal, feeling that animal represents his spirit...and he maintains a special connection with all animals, being able to call upon their spirits to aid him.

Advantages:
* may summon a special 'spirit' animal once per day per 5 levels of experience.  Spirit animal is randomly selected from 'spirit bear', 'spirit wolf', 'spirit lion' and 'spirit snake'.

Disadvantages:
* cannot shapeshift~
@25225 = ~SHAPESHIFTER: These druids master their shapechanging abilities much earlier than others and train intensely, gaining some unusual metamorphic powers.

Advantages:
* may shapechange into normal forms, as well as those of sword spider, baby wyvern and lesser basilisk

Disadvantages:
* may not wear better than leather armor~
