@25465 = ~Why, hello there.  I heard there were strangers in town.  Welcome.  Baldemar Thurlow, at your service.  What sort of business brings you to Lonelywood?~
@25466 = ~I see.  Well, it certainly is reassuring to have a brave band of adventurers such as yourselves in town.  If those hairy brutes do decide to attack Lonelywood, we'll need every sword we can get to aid in the defense.~
@25467 = ~You've been informed correctly.  I am the town's duly elected representative to the council.  Why do you ask?~
@25468 = ~I can tell you the situation is grim.  The barbarians have raised an army and are marching against the Ten-Towns.  Our town is cut off from aid, and we can expect no reinforcements in the near future.~
@25469 = ~Camp, you say?  Hmm... I'm afraid I don't know anything about that.~
@25470 = ~I admire your courage, but there really is no need for you to risk your lives by getting involved.  I assure you... the council is doing everything it can to prevent this war.~
@25471 = ~The council has dispatched an... uh... a delegate to meet with the barbarian king.  I'm sure he is well on his way to negotiating a peaceful settlement to this conflict.~
@25472 = ~Why, yes.  As a matter of fact, he was.  He stopped here in Lonelywood on his way to the barbarian camp.  As the town representative, I thought it my duty to aid his mission by providing food and lodging.~
@25473 = ~That's a good question.  To be honest, I haven't the slightest clue how he made it through.  He arrived alone, though.  Perhaps he managed to slip past the barbarians undetected.~
@25474 = ~Of course I knew *about* it.  If my memory serves me, you specifically asked if I knew the location of the camp.  I do not.  The delegate did not share that information with me.~
@25475 = ~Zaviera~
@25476 = ~Zaviera~
@25477 = ~Certainly.  What is it you wish to know?~
@25478 = ~Belmin Gergas~
@25479 = ~Belmin Gergas~
@25480 = ~Assassin?  Don't be ridiculous.  Who has been filling your heads with such lies?~
@25481 = ~Radeel~
@25482 = ~He's a filthy barbarian!  Their kind cannot be trusted.~
@25483 = ~Radeel~
@25484 = ~Even if these accusations were true, you cannot prove that I had anything to do with it.~
@25485 = ~All right, all right... it's true.  An assassin *was* hired to kill the barbarian leader.  But I swear to you, it wasn't my idea.  They made me go along with it.~
@25486 = ~Last month, the council met to discuss reports of a new barbarian king who was rallying the tribes to make war on the Ten-Towns.  As usual, none of the towns could agree on a course of action.~
@25487 = ~Yarin~
@25488 = ~Yarin~
@25489 = ~As a matter of fact, the meeting had to be adjourned prematurely to prevent arguments from escalating into fisticuffs.~
@25490 = ~Lost Child~
@25491 = ~Lost Child~
@25492 = ~Crazy Celvan~
@25493 = ~Crazy Celvan~
@25494 = ~Sooty Ball~
@25495 = ~Stone Spit~
@25496 = ~Salt Crystals~
@25497 = ~Water Jet~
@25498 = ~Boiling Rain Storm~
@25499 = ~Mist Ball~
@25500 = ~Magma Ball~ [BRANW37]
@25501 = ~Flame Jet~
@25502 = ~That same night, several of the council members, myself included, met in secret to discuss the matter further.  It was during this meeting that the assassination plot was proposed.~
@25503 = ~Of course, I was naturally opposed to such a dishonorable solution, but the others told me I had no choice.   They threatened to use their influence to remove me from the council if I didn't go along with the plan.~
@25504 = ~I was instructed to return to home at once and not to say a word to anyone about the plot.  They said that they would handle the hiring of the assassin, and that I need only to act as the killer's contact in Lonelywood.~
@25505 = ~Several nights later, the one-eyed stranger showed up at my door.  He said only that he was sent by the council, and that he was in need of lodging.~
@25506 = ~I was terrified that someone would see us together, so I invited him in.  He seemed a decent enough fellow.  We spoke a great deal that night - mostly about politics in the Dale, for I was too fearful to bring up the topic of the assassination plot.  The next morning, he left for the camp, and I never saw him again.~
@25507 = ~That's all I know.  You've got to believe me... I didn't want to have any part of this assassination business, but I had no choice.  The others would have ruined me if I opposed them.~
@25508 = ~I suppose you're right.  I've acted like a selfish coward.  I should've exposed this treachery before the council when I had the chance.~
@25509 = ~You've got a point.  I *am* still a council representative.  And as such, I believe it is my duty to report this matter before the entire council at our next meeting.  Thank you for making that clear to me.  ~
@25510 = ~I've told you the truth!  I swear on my mother's grave!~
@25511 = ~Murders?  Oh, you mean the animal attacks.  Poor Digby and Dolan.  It does seem a bit odd that they would both meet their ends in the same manner - and so close to one another.  Oh well... I'm sure Emmerich has the matter well in hand.~
@25512 = ~Yes, it was Digby I believe... or was it Doogal?  I can't remember.  In any case, I heard he was set upon by some wild beast.  A wolf, no doubt.  I shall have to talk to Emmerich about it.~
@25513 = ~Emmerich is our local bowyer.  He's lived in these parts for quite some time.  Knows the forest like the back of his hand.  Quite the woodsman, that Emmerich.~
@25514 = ~He has a cabin in the southeast corner of town, just past the Shrine of Waukeen.~
@25515 = ~Welcome back, my friends.  What can I do for you this day?~
@25516 = ~We are here to prevent a war between the barbarian tribes and the Ten-Towns.~
@25517 = ~Is it true that you sit on the council of the Ten-Towns?~
@25518 = ~Our business is our own.  Farewell.~
@25519 = ~Perhaps you can tell us more about the barbarian threat?~
@25520 = ~Slave Boy~
@25521 = ~Slave Boy~
@25522 = ~We've learned the barbarians have a camp nearby.  Do you know where it is?~
@25523 = ~Don't worry.  We've learned the location of the nearby barbarian camp, and we're heading out there to see if we can stop them.~
@25524 = ~We'll be glad to help in any way we can.  Farewell.~
@25525 = ~We've been to the barbarian camp.  We know about the assassin that was hired by the council.~
@25526 = ~Slave Girl~
@25527 = ~We've been to the barbarian camp.  Their king, Wylfdene, is under the impression that the council has conspired to assassinate him.~
@25528 = ~Slave Girl~
