@25538 = ~I see.  Perhaps you can tell us more about the barbarian threat?~
@25539 = ~I guess we'll just have to find the camp on our own.~
@25540 = ~And just what exactly is the council doing about all this?~
@25541 = ~Trust in your council if you like, but I'll not leave my fate in the hands of petty bureaucrats.  Good day.~
@25542 = ~I hope you're right.  Farewell, Baldemar.~
@25543 = ~We heard you had a guest several nights ago.  Was this one-eyed stranger the council delegate you speak of?~
@25544 = ~We've been to the barbarian camp.  We know this "delegate" was an assassin that was hired by the council.~
@25545 = ~We've been to the barbarian camp.  Their king, Wylfdene, is under the impression that the delegate was an assassin sent by the council to assassinate him.~
