@26036 = ~I digs hole for trapper killed in woods.  I thinks him called Digby.  He sleeps now... happy in hole I digs for him.~
@26037 = ~I digs another hole today.  Lots of holes lately.  Soon I runs out of room.~
@26038 = ~Other trapper... Dolan.  Wolf kills him too.  Not much left after wolf eats him.  But I digs him a good hole anyway.~
@26039 = ~No!  I digs no more holes!  I gets blisters from so many holes!~
@26040 = ~Hole for Doogal.  Him dies just like the others.  This place bad.  More holes than peoples.~
@26041 = ~Ah, the saviors of Lonelywood have returned.  I'm glad you're here, actually.  It saves me the trouble of having to track you down.~
@26042 = ~Just tying up a few loose ends.  Disposing of that bumbling wagon maker and his snobbish wife was hardly worth the effort, but in my line of work it pays to keep things nice and tidy.~
@26043 = ~I had no choice.  They knew too much.  If word got out that someone else had fulfilled my contract for me, my reputation as an assassin would be tarnished.  It's bad for business, you see.~
@26044 = ~Clever disguise, was it not?  Although, I must say I was growing rather tired of the charade.  All that digging was giving me blisters.  And that stupid girl child!  If that little brat only knew how close she came to death.  One more briarcone lobbed in my direction, and I swear I would've sliced her throat.~
@26045 = ~Because I'm an assassin, you dolt.  I needed to keep a low profile while in town.  A proper assassination takes time, you know.  There's a lot of planning involved.  You have to lie low, gather information on the mark, then strike when they least expect it.~
@26046 = ~I was just about to make my move when that delegate from the Ten-Towns arrived in Lonelywood.  That buffoon Baldemar mistook him for the assassin hired to kill the barbarian king.  The two morons nearly ruined it for me.~
@26047 = ~After the barbarians tortured and killed the delegate, they doubled the guards around the camp, making it next to impossible for me to sneak in make the kill.  Fortunately for me, you arrived and did the job for me.~
@26048 = ~Thank you.  Now that Wylfdene is dead and gone, all that remains for me to do is collect my fee.  Of course, you understand that I'll have to dispose of you as well.  I can't have you running about, telling everyone that it was you who killed the barbarian king, now can I?~
@26049 = ~But... there is a time and place for everything.  I fear now I must take my leave of you.  I have a few "errands" to run before I leave town.  But I'll be seeing you soon, I promise.  Very soon.  Farewell.~
