@26358 = ~Stop being so dramatic, Murdaugh.  Your silver tongue may be a bit tarnished from all the wine, but we still manage to squeeze a few good performances out of you from time to time.~
@26359 = ~Aye, 'tis strange, yet well deserved.  You see, the original owner of this inn was a less than reputable man who-~
@26360 = ~Yes.  'Tis said that he was fond of using that dead tree out front as a sort of impromptu gallows.  Back then, the Inn was known as Skeld's Place.  However, it didn't take long for word of Skeld's cruelty to spread.~
@26361 = ~However, that unfortunate business is all in the past.  Skeld is dead and buried, and now I am the proprietor of this inn.  The only legacy that remains of Skeld's brief, yet brutal, tenure is the establishment's name... the Whistling Gallows Inn.~
