@26463 = ~Hail and well met, strangers.  My name is Varglann, humble scribe and scholar from the city of Luskan.  I have just arrived in your lovely town on an errand of great importance.  Perhaps you would be so kind as to furnish me with some information that may aid me in my task?~
@26464 = ~My means of travel are not important.  On the other hand, the business that brings us to Lonelywood is *very* important.~
@26465 = ~The Bridge District~
@26466 = ~I seek an old colleague of mine.  I heard he may have relocated somewhere in this region.  I thought perhaps I would drop in and surprise him... you know, to catch up on old times and such.~
@26467 = ~His name is Alacander, though I wouldn't be surprised if he's changed his name.  Ever has he been the fickle one.  You would surely remember him if you've met him.  He's a thin, dark haired man in his late forties.  He is also a mage of considerable skill.~
@26468 = ~An innkeeper?  Ha!  Very clever, my old friend... though not clever enough, I'm afraid.  He's at the inn!  You all know what to do!  And remember... no witnesses!~
@26469 = ~Hold!  I mean... please, do not leave just yet.  My business here is quite urgent, and I do not have much time.  I would *appreciate* any information that would help me locate my long lost colleague.  ~
@26470 = ~That won't be necessary, Apheus.  Their attempt at deception merely confirms my suspicion that Alacander is somewhere in the area.  It is only a matter of time before we discover where he has hidden himself.~
@26471 = ~Now... I'm feeling particularly generous today, so I'm going to offer you a deal.  You will tell us exactly where to find our friend, and, in exchange, I promise that no one in this town shall come to harm.  What say you?~
@26472 = ~Calm yourself, Alpheus.  There's no need for such heavy-handed tactics.  These folk seem reasonable enough.  Surely they see that it is in their best interest to cooperate.~
@26473 = ~::Sigh::  Why must they always be so difficult?~
@26474 = ~Very well.  But dispatch them quickly.  Alacander cannot be far off.  The sooner we find him, the sooner we can remove his traitorous heart and return it to the Hosttower.~
@26475 = ~They are lying.  It seems they lack the proper motivation for telling the truth.  Perhaps if I killed one of them...~
@26476 = ~You're wasting your time, Vaarglan.  It's obvious these buffoons know nothing of Alacander.  I say we burn down this pathetic excuse for a town and slaughter its inhabitants.  If the traitor *is* here, such a display would surely draw him out.~
@26477 = ~Difficult suits me fine.  Shall we kill them now?~
@26478 = ~Just arrived, eh?  Tell me, how'd you manage to get past the barbarians camped in Bremen's Run?~
@26479 = ~~
@26480 = ~What kind of information do you seek?~
@26481 = ~Not interested.  Farewell.~
@26482 = ~Us?  I take it you are not alone?~
@26483 = ~And what sort of business may that be?~
@26484 = ~Best of luck to you, then.  Farewell.~
@26485 = ~Who is this colleague you seek?~
@26486 = ~Sorry, we can't help you.  Farewell.~
@26487 = ~I know of no mages in Lonelywood.  You must have the wrong town.~
@26488 = ~A mage, eh?  Kieran, the innkeeper of the Whistling Gallows, certainly fits that description.  Perhaps he's the one you seek.~
@26489 = ~Very well.  Who is this colleague you seek?~
@26490 = ~And *I* would appreciate you stepping aside so we can go about our business.~
@26491 = ~Sorry, I can't help you.  Now if you don't mind, we've business of our own to tend to.~
@26492 = ~I'd sooner strike a deal with a pit-fiend.  Now, I suggest you and your lackey leave town before I shove that wand so far up your robes, you'll be coughing up fireballs for weeks.~
@26493 = ~Very well... since you'll probably find him anyway.  I believe Kieran, the innkeeper at the Whistling Gallows, may be the man you seek.~
